(595, 2, '2022-10-02 23:12:18', '2022-10-02 20:12:18', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even Ferrari is not immune from switching to electric traction, it has been promised to build its first fully electric car by 2025. But until all the cars of the iconic brand become electric, the world will receive some special models as a sign of respect for the internal combustion engine, which is based on the accumulated knowledge of Ferrari.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The 812 Competizione is exactly what is a limited, tuned and honed version of the already ballistic superfast 812. The car is also available in a convertible body and costs 44.7 million rubles before choosing options. But even if someone can afford it, they are too late. All copies of the machines have already been sold.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The specification is frankly appetizing. The 6.5-liter V12 Ferrari was accelerated to 819 hp and equipped with new titanium connecting rods, new pistons, crankshaft and intake manifold.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The dual-clutch gearbox was recalibrated for a five percent gearshift speed, and independent steering on the rear wheels required a new version of the Ferrari side-slip control system. The car is 38 kg lighter than the standard 812, and its redesigned body provides greater downforce.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The engine bursts into life, capturing the thoughts of motorists. It reacts quickly to the pedal and pulls well even at low revs, and gives a wild acceleration.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, a big V12 can give more, the exhaust sound has already turned into a piercing scream, and the speed is growing incredibly fast, it seems that it just has to burst. But this is not the case, and only when the gearshift indicators start flashing at the top of the steering wheel, when the 9500 rpm speed limiter turns on, we grab the right paddle and select the next gear.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ferrari can accelerate from a standstill to 100 km/h in just 2.9 seconds: really fast.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The steering is light and very fast. The nose rushes into the corner, but the rear of the car does not tend to skid – at least until you turn down the power a little earlier, and then the sticky Michelin tires begin to slip. The brakes are also clearly capable of restraining the car, regardless of its power.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Review of Ferrari 812 2021', 'Even Ferrari is not immune from switching to electric traction, it has been promised to build its first fully electric car by 2025. But until all the cars of the iconic brand become electric, the world will receive some special models as a sign of respect for the internal combustion engine, which is based on the accumulated knowledge of Ferrari.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'review-of-ferrari-812-2021', '', '', '2022-10-02 23:12:18', '2022-10-02 20:12:18', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=595', 0, 'post', '', 0),
