(600, 2, '2022-10-02 23:19:32', '2022-10-02 20:19:32', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Maranello has long established itself as a standard of surreal automotive art, but accessible for medium-engined performance. Cars like the F8 Tributo and the news 90 showcase Ferrari\'s technological and artistic talent, and link its road cars to Formula 1.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With Maranello front-engined cars, it\'s not always that simple. The amazing V12 812 Superfast is often mixed up with the GT, but there is really nothing like it, instead the car is a hypercar that is always ready to sweep sideways in one throttle breath and force a fresh look at the concept of \"fast\". And then there is the Portofino, an entry-level Maranello model with a folding hard top. In many ways, the least Ferrari-like car money can buy is also the first Ferrari to be purchased by a mass buyer.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And now there is a new Ferrari Uomo (Ferrari Roma), a 2+2 coupe, introduced at the end of 2019. Beautiful and fragrant of the past in its ideals, but fortunately, in its design. The Ferrari Roma (17.1 million rubles) costs slightly more than the Portofino (16.6 million rubles) and promises to be both a GT and a sports car, as well as the first of a new breed of Ferrari suitable for everyday use. Well, we\'ll see.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>So, \"Ferrari Roma\" is a Portofino with a welded roof?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Partly, but a lot of what distinguishes these two cars is well suited for Roma sports cars. The aluminum body structure is based on the Portofino design – the same wheelbase, for example – but Maranello claims that 70% of the body and other structures are new or substantially modified (the lion\'s share of these 70% is accounted for by the new body). The weight has decreased by about 100 kg, and the center of gravity has become lower due to the removal of the bulky folding mechanism of the Portofino roof.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thus, the weight became less, and he moved closer to the floor. This, in turn, allowed the Ferrari to operate at the same speeds on the front springs as the Portofino, and the rear springs are 10% softer, while reducing the body roll by 10% with similar lateral acceleration — all this is good news.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Customers will also receive the latest Maranello driver assistance system, Slide Slip Control 6.0 and Ferrari Dynamic Enhancer. It is also the first Ferrari GT to receive proper underbody aerodynamics with vortex generators in the floor to create useful downforce, despite the conspicuous absence of spoilers on a very smooth body.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Is there anything new?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Plenty. The V8 Roma is not exactly a new car, being closely related to Portofino, but it is equipped with a new valve actuator and more aggressive cams with increased lift, an exhaust system with reduced back pressure and sensors that allow Ferrari to safely squeeze another 5,000 rpm from two turbines. The net result would be good, 35-40 hp more powerful compared to 592 hp at Portofino, if Roma were not also required to have gasoline particulate filters, which reduce this preferential power to 19 hp, in total Roma develops 611 hp.. This is a huge performance for one of the \"entry-level\" Ferrari models…</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The engine runs through a new eight-speed gearbox taken from the SF90, only 6 kg lighter, which is faster and more efficient than the Portofino seven-speed automatic, with a dry crankcase layout to reduce losses. The gear ratios from first to seventh gear are shorter than those of Portofino for stronger acceleration, while the eighth offers lazy overdrive.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Inside, the Roma gets a brand new spacious interior, with stylish curves and a welcome sense of minimalism. There is also the infotainment system of the new generation of Ferrari, which debuted in the SF 90. You grab the new steering wheel (not the most beautiful, too large and with an abundance of plastic, but with intuitive functionality, including a touch panel on the right spoke, with which you can navigate through the menu on the driver\'s display) and look at the 16-inch multifunctional curved display capable of demonstrating three options of \"instruments\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The center stack has a new 8.4-inch touchscreen with portrait orientation, which looks a bit cheap considering the price of the car, but at least everything works quite nicely.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Built for comfort or speed?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is comfort here, although the Roma is not an S-class cabin. The seats and driving position remain comfortable for many drivers throughout the day (but taller pilots complained about the lack of altitude margin, and we found that the RHD pedal arrangement is slightly shifted), and the interior carries a huge sense of celebration.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Exhaust gas noise is always present and can grind on boring roads after a while, but there is less road noise in the cabin than can be expected, given the amount of rubber, or rather its proximity to the ears of the driver and passengers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Ferrari Roma Review: The new Maranello 2+2 Coupe', 'Maranello has long established itself as a standard of surreal automotive art, but accessible for medium-engined performance. Cars like the F8 Tributo and the news 90 showcase Ferrari\'s technological and artistic talent, and link its road cars to Formula 1.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'ferrari-roma-review-the-new-maranello-22-coupe', '', '', '2022-10-02 23:19:32', '2022-10-02 20:19:32', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=600', 0, 'post', '', 0),
