(603, 2, '2022-10-02 23:24:38', '2022-10-02 20:24:38', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As a potential farewell to the Ferrari V12 production engine in pure gasoline form, the 812 GTS is a fitting symbol that remains true to the brand\'s values. The performance is really amazing, but it is the way the car disposes of it, and the sensations that it causes as part of the driving experience, that make it simply impossible not to fall in love with this car. Yes, there are some technologies and interior elements that now look and feel a little outdated, but in almost all other respects, the 812 GTS is the best front—engined supersport car, but at the same time one of the best Grand Tours. Bravo Ferrari.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We know that the days of internal combustion engines are numbered, especially engines of higher power. Their service life will be slightly increased with the mass electrification of cars, but the life cycle of the atmospheric V12 Ferrari may be over long before the end of the decade.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thus, if the 812 GTS is a serial swan song for the iconic Ferrari V12 internal combustion engine, then all of its 29.3 million rubles worth should be savored, because it is a fantastic sports car dominated by this engine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is a 6.5-liter V12 that produces a whopping 800 horsepower (789bhp), which is symbolized by the eight in the 812 name. Along with this, there are 718 Nm of torque, and 80% of them are available from just 3500 rpm. Who needs turbines?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The car is incredibly quiet, at least with the roof and windows closed, but after the Mechanical Ballet with the opening of the rigid roof, the situation changes so that the ears are ready to explode when the iconic V12 roar fills the cabin. The exhaust pipe has been specially tuned for the GTS for exactly this purpose.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The roof is more like a Porsche Targa-style panel: it is powered by an electric motor and the opening takes 14 seconds, and this procedure can be initiated at speeds up to 50 km/h.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>That\'s just because of the weight of the roof engines, the mechanism and the additional reinforcement of the body, the GTS has become heavier by about 120 kg, but only 1625 kg is not so much, it almost does not affect the performance of the 812.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The GTS will accelerate from a standstill to 100 km/h in 3.0 seconds, according to Ferrari, and acceleration from a standstill to 200 km/ h will take only 8.3 seconds. This is an amazing pace for an open—top car without turbines - and it really feels like it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the race mode selected on the Manettino dial on the steering wheel, the throttle response, ironically, becomes almost like an electric car. Millimeters in the movement of the gas pedal are reflected by the instantaneous response of the engine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, in an open—top form, the 812 is not just a power plant. The chassis is equal to this engine. The steering works as fast as we used to expect from Ferrari, but working with the GTS platform means that, despite the roof cut, the torsional rigidity of the car feels excellent, and the front part copes with the steering speed without any problems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The clutch level on the front axle is at the level for the race track. The slightly weighted electric steering is almost not felt, but the way the long nose of the car rushes to the corner fills with confidence, even in such a large car, with such great power and such an expensive price.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The GTS\'s absolute maneuverability is facilitated by the second generation of the so-called virtual rear axle steering with a short wheelbase. Basically, the rear wheels work to help the front ones.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At the rear, the grip and traction are surprisingly good, considering the level of performance, and the relatively conservative Pirelli P Zero tires work well on our warm March day. However, the GTS actually performs better in the “CT Off” driving mode, which uses the excellent Ferrari Side Slip Control 5.0 chassis system, allowing you to play with the balance of the car.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After a series of turns and just one short straight, all the straight lines seem short in the GTS, it becomes obvious that the car offers supersport characteristics. And when there\'s just a desire to relax, Ferrari\'s flagship open-top car is a great car for a cruise, proving its GT reputation: it\'s the perfect combination of aggression and serenity.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the roof down, turbulence in the cabin is not so great, which is facilitated by two small visors on the windshield, which help deflect air over the top of the open cabin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As for practicality and overall usability, the 210-liter trunk offers enough space for a couple of weekend bags, while forward visibility is pretty good, thanks to the low nose. Nevertheless, this is a very long, very wide car, and the buttresses, although they look great, they really worsen visibility from behind a little.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The infotainment system displays that flank the central analog rev counter now look a bit old-fashioned and grainy in their resolution, and the menu system is also not the most intuitive to navigate.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In fact, it wouldn\'t hurt to refresh the whole salon. The quality of the material is certainly good, but the design is a little outdated compared to the latest Ferrari GT Roma car.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'New review of the Ferrari 812 GTS 2021', 'As a potential farewell to the Ferrari V12 production engine in pure gasoline form, the 812 GTS is a fitting symbol that remains true to the brand\'s values. The performance is really amazing, but it is the way the car disposes of it, and the sensations that it causes as part of the driving experience, that make', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'new-review-of-the-ferrari-812-gts-2021', '', '', '2022-10-02 23:24:38', '2022-10-02 20:24:38', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=603', 0, 'post', '', 0),
