(609, 2, '2022-10-04 22:08:45', '2022-10-04 19:08:45', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The BMW X1 is the smallest crossover of the German brand, a subcompact luxury car that, like many of its direct competitors, looks more like a tall hatchback than an SUV. In 2023, the brand new X1 will change its appearance to a more off-road one. The car has become 4 centimeters taller, 3 cm longer and 2 cm wider. In addition to changing the dimensions, BMW designers have changed the body shape of the X1, giving the roof line and hood a more vertical appearance, which, combined with a new larger radiator grille, gives the car a more confident profile, like the larger X3 and X5.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Under its new body, the X1 remains almost the same as before. At the start, one version is available, the X1 xDrive28i, which is an all-wheel drive car equipped with a 2.0-liter turbocharged I-4 engine. BMW has overhauled the engine, transferring it to work on the Miller combustion cycle. Power has increased to 241 hp and 400 Nm of torque (from 228 hp and 350 Nm) and is transmitted to all four wheels using a new seven-speed dual-clutch automatic transmission with fully electronic drive. The M Sport models are equipped with paddle switches behind the steering wheel for manual gear selection, with the Sport Boost function provided, thanks to which pressing the right paddle for a long time switches all transmission and chassis settings \"to the most aggressive, \"for the fastest acceleration.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The new look of the SUV is emphasized by standard 18-inch wheels, and a 20-inch option is available in the M Sport configuration for the first time. BMW also revised the front suspension of the X1, increasing the wheel angle by 15 percent in search of a better steering feel and better control on the highway. The multi-link rear suspension separates the springs and shock absorbers, which BMW says improves the axle layout and thus opens up more interior and cargo space. The sportier version of the M Sport uses a faster steering gear ratio, as well as frequency-selective shock absorbers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>New BMW inside</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>No matter how large-scale the changes in appearance are, the X1 is undergoing drastic changes inside: a higher fit corresponds to a taller body, as well as a large, slightly curved new touchscreen and digital dashboard perfectly match each other. The displays are located amidst a riot of materials and textures of the interior. The orange model shown in the photo has speaker grilles with a cross pattern, chrome inclusions around unusual central air vents, plastic trim with a thin stripe on the center console, stitched leather trim and much more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When switching to the BMW iDrive 8 X1 operating system, it abandons the iDrive control knob of the old model on the center console in favor of a fully touch interface and voice control. In fact, the X1 loses almost all of its physical buttons on the dashboard — where the previous X1 provided users with knobs and buttons, say, for radio presets, air conditioning control, etc., In this 2023 version, the only obvious buttons are buttons on the steering wheel, door panels (for controlling windows and locks), as well as lighting controls to the left of the steering wheel. A floating console panel in front of the central armrest provides a convenient location for the ignition button, gear shift joystick, parking brake and alarm buttons, as well as a large wheel for volume control. Everything else is handled on a 10.25-inch digital touchscreen.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Technologization does not end there. BMW offers the \"smartphone as a key\" option, as well as a new digital user identification (your BMW ID), with the storage of seat memory, shortcuts on the screen and navigation settings through the BMW app. By entering the car using this BMW ID using a smartphone, the car adapts all the preset parameters to the user.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As always, the X1 has many safety features built in, including standard direct collision warning, automatic emergency braking, lane departure warning, parking sensors and blind spot monitoring. The additional Driving Assistant Professional function will provide advanced adaptive cruise control functions, including automatic lane keeping and the ability to stop the BMW completely and accelerate again in traffic. Driving without the help of hands will be possible even in conditions of heavy traffic on motorways, provided that the speed of X1 does not exceed 60 km/h.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Prices for the new model will be announced soon, but we found out that even the basic X1 will receive a standard navigation system, SiriusXM, dual-zone automatic climate control, an electric trunk door, LED headlights and 18-inch wheels. Additional packages include Design xLine (wheel and trim upgrades), Convenience (Digital key, panoramic sunroof, wireless charger), Professional Driving Assistance (the aforementioned advanced adaptive cruise control and lane keeping features), Shadowline (dark color trim), Premium (Universal garage door key, panoramic sunroof, display, Harman/Kardon audio system, wireless charger, mirrors with automatic dimming, surround view camera, parking assistant) and M Sport (18-, 19- or 20-inch wheels, gear shift buttons for the steering wheel, sports seats, steering wheel M, body kit, Shadowline trim). Autonomous options include heated seats, heated steering wheel, trailer hitch (which may not be available at launch), sports seats and various interior trim.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In addition to the luxurious equipment and additional power, a more confident body shape and style should help the X1 to get out of the shadow of the segment of small luxury SUVs.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'First Look BMW X1 2023', 'The BMW X1 is the smallest crossover of the German brand, a subcompact luxury car that, like many of its direct competitors, looks more like a tall hatchback than an SUV. In 2023, the brand new X1 will change its appearance to a more off-road one. The car has become 4 centimeters taller, 3 cm longer and 2 cm wider. In addition to changing the dimensions, BMW designers have changed the body shape of the X1, giving the roof line and hood a more vertical appearance, which, combined with a new larger radiator grille, gives the car a more confident profile, like the larger X3 and X5.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'first-look-bmw-x1-2023', '', '', '2022-10-04 22:08:45', '2022-10-04 19:08:45', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=609', 0, 'post', '', 0),
