olid walnut is used for the decoration of the gearshift knob and in the interior trim, and the Victor steering wheel is a redesigned version of the motorsport unit installed on the Vulcan.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Once the Victor\'s platform and aerodynamics were finalized, Aston Martin added many chassis components from the track-only Vulcan, including its internal springs and shock absorbers, central locking hubs and a six-piston carbon-ceramic Brembo braking system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All the power is generated by an atmospheric 7.3-liter V12, which produces a staggering 836 hp and 821 Nm of torque. The supercar has rear-wheel drive via a six-speed manual transmission. Thus, the Victor is the most powerful manual sports car ever built by Aston Martin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Aston Martin Victor — the most powerful supercar to order', 'This is the Aston Martin Victor — a supercar created according to an individual project of a private customer, implemented by the own engineering division of the British firm Q by Aston Martin.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '615-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-10-04 22:24:23', '2022-10-04 19:24:23', '', 615, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=617', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(618, 2, '2022-10-04 22:35:28', '2022-10-04 19:35:28', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Late in the evening, we are racing at freeway speeds when we see a knot of taillight ribbons ahead. Time to shift gears in the Audi S3 2022. As its 2.0-liter turbocharged inline-four engine revs around 5,000 rpm, digital sensors pulse and a hum comes from the blackened exhaust pipes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Relying on the powerful S3 brakes, which are able to stop the entry-level Audi sports sedan from 100 km/h to 0 in an impressive 32.9 meters. We step on the gas again, the seven-speed automatic transmission S3 with two clutches switches almost to the red level, and we rush home, enjoying the luxurious leather interior.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The line between a sporty and a luxury car is increasingly blurred as premium brands such as Audi continue to refine and rethink cars such as the updated S3.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Audi S3 Tests</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By the way, the first impressions of our test team from the updated S3 were positive. The aforementioned 2.0-liter S3 turbo engine with 306 horsepower and 300 Nm of torque is an engine that the team called \"vigorous\", with a good average power of 3,000 rpm. This is a four-cylinder engine that is more than capable of confidently accelerating a one-and-a-half-ton S3 100 km/h in 4.6 seconds. And 400 meters (a quarter of a mile) is overcome in 13.2 seconds at a speed of 169.3 km /h.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One of the closest competitors of the S3 with Quattro all-wheel drive in this segment is the Mercedes-AMG A35 4Matic. A slightly lighter (1,578 kg) A35, which we tested with a 2.0-liter AMG turbo engine with 302 horsepower, overtook the new S3 in a straight line: 4.4 seconds to 100 km/h and a quarter mile in 13.1 seconds. But in our testing, the S3 braked earlier than the A35 — 32.9 versus 34.1 meters.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>S3 Dynamics</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As for dynamics and handling, our \"eight\" test was completed in 25.5 seconds at a lateral acceleration of 0.71 g (on average). Although the A35 is a clear winner in terms of dynamics.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Our road test editor Ilya Levitsky said that the S3 reminded him of another new German car, the eighth-generation Volkswagen GTI, and this is not surprising, given that both are based on the Volkswagen Group\'s MEB Evo platform. But he noted that the S3 \"has a little more advantages, good engine sound and better grip, reliable brakes on every lap and good skid grip. It reduces power pretty well on the way out of the turn with a slight hint of understeer, which disappears when we turn the steering wheel.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ilya said that although the S3 transmission was \"incredibly smooth\" on the upshift, he had problems switching to a downshift, and he had to resort to manual mode because the car was incorrectly switching to a downshift when he maneuvered on our site.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Quiet interior and lots of options</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the open road, the Audi S3 of 2022 demonstrates some rigidity when hitting asphalt defects, but there is nothing unusual for such a car. Like other Audi\'s, the S3 is equipped with a drive mode selection system that improves gear shifting and other factors, such as the steering feel, which, according to Ilya, was heavy in dynamic mode, but you can adjust the steering in individual mode and adjust the feedback to your liking.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One thing that can be noticed at speed is how isolated the stylized and high—tech interior of the S3 is. For a compact sports sedan, this is even too much, but this is a controversial point, since it demonstrates the luxurious side of this car.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By the way, the Audi S3 of 2022 meets most of the requirements that can be imposed on a car priced from $ 45,945. The S3 also looks like a sports car with aggressive handling of the front and rear panels and a slightly lower fit than its A3 counterpart. However, those who have a desire to further improve the car, there is a Premium Plus package worth $ 2,800 (adaptive cruise control, advanced safety and convenience features) and a technology package worth $ 2,250 (Audi virtual cockpit with a 12.3-inch screen, Bang &amp; Olufsen sound).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This particular car was also equipped with three additional interior and exterior styling packages, the highlight of which is the $1950 Black Optic package, which darkens several trim elements and adds 19-inch performance wheels/tires. All this black color contrasts pleasantly with the red metallic paint of Tango.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This test car, priced at $55,890, is expensive, although it does not differ from its German counterparts equipped with the same options. But even in the basic configuration, the S3 2022 model provides more than enough attractiveness and performance to satisfy customers looking for something special in the more affordable part of the Audi lineup.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Audi S3 2022 Test drive: a cross between a sporty and a luxury sedan', 'Late in the evening, we are racing at freeway speeds when we see a knot of taillight ribbons ahead. Time to shift gears in the Audi S3 2022. As its 2.0-liter turbocharged inline-four engine revs around 5,000 rpm, digital sensors pulse and a hum comes from the blackened exhaust pipes.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'audi-s3-2022-test-drive-a-cross-between-a-sporty-and-a-luxury-sedan', '', '', '2022-10-04 22:35:28', '2022-10-04 19:35:28', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=618', 0, 'post', '', 0),
