(627, 2, '2022-11-19 16:18:44', '2022-11-19 13:18:44', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bentley claims that this elongated luxury SUV will gain a huge market share. After a little test drive, we understand why.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bentley is nothing but pragmatism. Of course it should be present, given the prevailing economic winds hitting British luxury brands such as Aston Martin and Jaguar. But Bentley had a very good year, and Bentayga played a huge role in increasing the company\'s profits. To celebrate this event, the Crewe company took a short break and presented a variant of its impressive luxury SUV with an enlarged wheelbase (EWB). After spending some time with Bentayga EWB, it becomes clear that pragmatism pays dividends — along with a first-class, special feeling in the second row of EWB.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Slight stretching</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In a way, yes, EWB is a difficult task. Bentayga is suitable for those who prefer to sit in the back rather than in the driver\'s seat. Of course, some owners are attracted to driving, but there are not as many of them as you might think. Bentley has made some efforts to provide a larger—scale transformation than just cutting and pasting - 2.5 thousand new parts have been announced, a tricky rear steering system has been created and luxury options for the rear seats have been added.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The elongated wheelbase and roof visually distinguish the Bentayga, giving the car an impressive and elegant appearance. Smooth characteristic lines on the sides, a radiator grille with vertical blades borrowed from the mouth of the new Flying Spur, and a polished version of the 22-inch wheels add to the appeal. The unbalanced shapes of the doors—the huge back door overshadowing the much smaller front one-ruin the charm a bit. But it\'s inevitable when first-class rear passenger space (and access) is the main motivation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Great power</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The 542-horsepower EWB, which is only a tenth of a second slower in acceleration to 100 km/h than its shorter V8, leaves little doubt. The 98 extra kilograms of EWB that the motor carries on itself seem like a drop in a very large bucket — the total weight of the car now is 3249 kg, to be precise. At the moment, the 4.0-liter twin-turbocharged V-8 engine is the only engine available on the EWB version.: We\'re curious why Bentley didn\'t go with the affordable Bentayga W-12 engine, but maybe it will be redesigned into an even more exclusive version of this long SUV.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>More importantly, the dynamic balance has not changed much. Yes, the EWB is 17.7 cm longer, but the new rear steering system (the first on the Bentayga) made it possible to achieve a smaller turning radius than the Bentayga with a short wheelbase. Adding to this the magic of adjustable shock absorbers (which adjust from slightly softer than the usual Bentayga to the same rigid in sports mode) and standard 48-volt active stabilizer bars, we get a car that does not seem as long or massive as it really is — at least, from the driver\'s seat.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The huge mass of the EWB slightly reduces its performance. Bentley claims that the car accelerates to 100 km/h in 4.5 seconds, and there is no reason to doubt it, but the way it picks up speed … I immediately think of a steam locomotive, not an overgrown WRX. Power and torque are sufficient and easily accessible, and in sports mode, the exhaust emits a pleasant and majestic growl.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>First-class interior</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>From the back seat, it\'s hard to think about anything other than a huge space in which you can relax (and even lie down). Voluminous is not even the right word, the cabin is like first class in one of the ultra—exclusive long-haul airlines. The space inside is larger than that of the old Mulsanne sedan, which was even longer and which the EWB effectively replaces.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Although even the basic three-seat rear seats (as in a regular Bentayga) allow you to enjoy the space, more exclusive seating options are required: 4 + 1 and a four-seat arrangement to fully appreciate the convenience of the EWB. However, there is no option with a third row of seats, and despite the fact that there is stretching between the wheels, the rear luggage compartment has not changed compared to models with a short wheelbase.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The \"airplane seat\" for most probably evokes memories of the torture devices of economy class, but think instead of the softest business class throne, and then give it 22 forms of adjustment. Then add some useful features: for example, there is a system that uses sensors to automatically heat and cool the back and buttocks to the desired temperature, selected from six levels. Almost imperceptible swaying of massage bubbles to gently move the body for three hours. And most importantly, it is possible to recline 40 degrees to take a nice nap or just look up through a giant glass panel, breathing air purified by ionizers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>No less important for some customers, given the size of the rear doors, are the additional power drives of the rear doors. Their use is intuitive: pushing an open door, it will close with a deliberate speed. From the inside, pressing the button will close the door.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bentley worked harder on the EWB to overcome the terrible noise, vibration and stiffness that could result from modifications needed to create a longer, roomier and potentially more echo-reflective rear compartment. In the end, the glass both on top and on the sides became larger. The problem was solved from two sides: the acoustic coating on the glass was revised and the exhaust system was redesigned. By combining this with the redesigned shock absorber software, the softest tuning has become noticeably softer than on other Bentaygas, and as a result, a calmer experience.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>A new luxury</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>EWB is available in base, Azure and 1st Edition trim levels, each with additional options. The EWB has several innovations that deserve attention, including several intriguing and new options: a new pattern on the seats, interesting metal overlays applied manually to the trim, and ambient lighting \"Bentley Diamond Illumination\", which shines through the leather door cards, creating an interesting and impressive look.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bentley expects customers to eagerly load all additional options into their EWBS, including passenger seats, as well as additional paint and interior options. In addition, EWB provides additional options for further customization.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The EWB is significantly more expensive than its short—wheelbase counterparts - from $229,625 or $266,225 for an azure finish, and offers plenty of options and upgrades, such as Airline Seat. Bentley assumes that many customers will add about $40,000 to the base price of the selected EWB model — this figure is not difficult to understand, given the prices of some options. A four-seat cabin with airline seats? It will cost $14,915. But these costs will not only make it their own, but will also create an impressive appearance (and price tag), which embodied such a majestic car as the Mulsanne sedan.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Роскошный Bentley Bentayga EWB 2023: первый взгляд', 'Bentley claims that this elongated luxury SUV will gain a huge market share. After a little test drive, we understand why...', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', '%d1%80%d0%be%d1%81%d0%ba%d0%be%d1%88%d0%bd%d1%8b%d0%b9-bentley-bentayga-ewb-2023-%d0%bf%d0%b5%d1%80%d0%b2%d1%8b%d0%b9-%d0%b2%d0%b7%d0%b3%d0%bb%d1%8f%d0%b4', '', '', '2022-11-19 16:18:44', '2022-11-19 13:18:44', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=627', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(628, 1, '2022-11-19 16:18:01', '2022-11-19 13:18:01', '', '215-mmft-bentley-bentayga-ewb-2023-1-638-328-720x405', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '215-mmft-bentley-bentayga-ewb-2023-1-638-328-720x405', '', '', '2022-11-19 16:18:01', '2022-11-19 13:18:01', '', 627, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/215-mmft-bentley-bentayga-ewb-2023-1-638-328-720x405-1.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
