 roomier and potentially more echo-reflective rear compartment. In the end, the glass both on top and on the sides became larger. The problem was solved from two sides: the acoustic coating on the glass was revised and the exhaust system was redesigned. By combining this with the redesigned shock absorber software, the softest tuning has become noticeably softer than on other Bentaygas, and as a result, a calmer experience.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>A new luxury</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>EWB is available in base, Azure and 1st Edition trim levels, each with additional options. The EWB has several innovations that deserve attention, including several intriguing and new options: a new pattern on the seats, interesting metal overlays applied manually to the trim, and ambient lighting \"Bentley Diamond Illumination\", which shines through the leather door cards, creating an interesting and impressive look.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bentley expects customers to eagerly load all additional options into their EWBS, including passenger seats, as well as additional paint and interior options. In addition, EWB provides additional options for further customization.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The EWB is significantly more expensive than its short—wheelbase counterparts - from $229,625 or $266,225 for an azure finish, and offers plenty of options and upgrades, such as Airline Seat. Bentley assumes that many customers will add about $40,000 to the base price of the selected EWB model — this figure is not difficult to understand, given the prices of some options. A four-seat cabin with airline seats? It will cost $14,915. But these costs will not only make it their own, but will also create an impressive appearance (and price tag), which embodied such a majestic car as the Mulsanne sedan.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Роскошный Bentley Bentayga EWB 2023: первый взгляд', 'Bentley claims that this elongated luxury SUV will gain a huge market share. After a little test drive, we understand why...', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '627-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-11-19 16:18:44', '2022-11-19 13:18:44', '', 627, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=629', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(630, 2, '2022-11-19 16:26:31', '2022-11-19 13:26:31', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>How did it happen that this limited edition Bentley Mulliner Batur coupe, all 18 copies of which are sold out, and all 18 are equipped with a premium W-12 engine, represents the first ever all-electric car of the brand, which is due to appear in 2025?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The short answer is that the Batur, like the 2020 Bacalar, is a living concept car. Freed from the obligations of \"regular\" sales or normalized product release cycles, the Batur is a dazzling demonstration of all that Bentley has now and the future. So, although an internal combustion engine is installed in the engine compartment of the Batur, its layout allows you to look at what a Bentley could look like without internal combustion engines.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>\"Resting beast pose\"</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you study the Batur lines, the shape of the radiator grille, bumpers and much more, you can easily imagine how the exhaust pipes and the radiator grille can disappear without leaving the audience confused about what they are looking at. This is unmistakably Bentley, even if you replace the radiator grille with a one-piece, more aerodynamic panel and replace the exhaust pipes with two more aerodynamic diffuser channels. Designers give some tips: the Batur radiator grille can be closed without losing its majestic appearance — mainly because the inner part of the radiator grille seems to float inside the frame, surrounded by a recessed frame. On a full electric car, this ventilation trim (in combination with the lower and outer bumper vents) can be everything the car needs, with the central section largely overlapped for smoother aerodynamics.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bentley has also changed the proportions of the car, shifting the cabin backwards compared to the Continental GT coupe, on which this Batur is supposed to be based. To visually increase the length of the hood, the designers laid a lining under the side glass, which stretches almost to the corners of the radiator grille. According to the Bentley designers, the hunched, ready-to-fight appearance (according to them) resembles the \"stance of a resting beast\", like \"a lion or a tiger hiding in an attacking pose among the tall grass.\" If we consider it as a vehicle, and not as a cat\'s face, then the Batur looks accordingly bent and fast, even sitting still.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bentley considers this car as a kind of wires of its W-12 engine, therefore, the automaker made sure that this version of the engine was the most powerful ever offered. The 6.0-liter twelve-cylinder engine with an unusual configuration of the \"W\" cylinder block produces more than 730 hp and 1000 Nm of torque. Bentley Continental GT Speed — the actual top of the Continental line with the same engine develops \"only\" 626 hp and 900 Nm of torque. The powerful engine is paired with an eight-speed automatic transmission with dual clutch and an all-wheel drive system with electronic locking of the rear differential.<br>Underneath the rest of the Batur is essentially the same suspension as Bentley\'s Continental GT Speed. It has a more rigid adjustment of three-chamber pneumatic springs and adaptive shock absorbers, and also has steering on the rear wheels and an active 48-volt Bentley stabilizer bar system. In the similar Continental GT model, these components give relatively large and heavy two-door cars amazing maneuverability, keeping their body flat in turns and helping to turn faster.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Luxury is everywhere and everywhere</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Batur\'s athleticism is welcome, but in fact it exists as a precious treasure. For those lucky 18 owners, it\'s a kind of collectible diamond. Each Batur car is \"created\" together with its owner, who can choose everything from seat and interior materials to colors, finishes and much more (even specific components) during the hours—long customization process, which includes a digital preview. The choice of colors is literally described as \"endless\", and Bentley will even draw any graphics or design that the owner\'s heart desires. Elements such as trim and radiator grille can be \"any combination of light and dark, satin or glossy, or even titanium.\" Some of them, such as the radiator grille on the car pictured here, may even be a mixture of these things.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So that wealthy owners don\'t feel guilty about all this personalization - or because of the environmental impact of Honkin’ W—12 engine exhaust - Bentley has great news: eco-friendly options! Instead of carbon fiber exterior trim, you can choose a new composite material made of natural fibers, which resembles carbon fiber, but is positioned as an \"eco-friendly alternative\". The same can be said about some leather interior finishes, which can also be replaced with artificial suede if cowhide leather does not fit. In addition, it\'s hard to believe, but Bentley carpets are made from recycled yarn.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Some elements of the interior decoration, in addition to titanium, chrome or conventional materials, can even be printed on a 3D printer using 18-carat gold. And to show how free interior personalization can be, the dashboard of the debut Batur is decorated with panels that change color in the style of \"guitar fading\", and includes an illustration of a wave that apparently describes the noise produced by the engine. Again, this is a fully custom-built, hand-built car.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>After reading all this, you are probably wondering what the word \"Batur\" means. It is named after a very deep lake in Indonesia, formed from a crater. Bentley Mulliner coachbuilt\'s latest project, Bacalar topless, was also named after a deep natural water source. The name really doesn\'t matter, although it usefully serves as the final allegory of the tuning process faced by those 18 fans who are already queuing for the Batur: the choice is almost as bottomless as the lake after which this car is named.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Limited Edition Bentley Mulliner Batur: All sold Out', 'How did it happen that this limited edition Bentley Mulliner Batur coupe, all 18 copies of which are sold out, and all 18 are equipped with a premium W-12 engine, represents the first ever all-electric car of the brand, which is due to appear in 2025?', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'limited-edition-bentley-mulliner-batur-all-sold-out', '', '', '2022-11-19 16:27:01', '2022-11-19 13:27:01', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=630', 0, 'post', '', 0),
