(633, 2, '2022-11-19 16:32:46', '2022-11-19 13:32:46', '<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>This is the second Bentley model to receive a plug-in hybrid powertrain, and the trend towards hybridization will certainly continue.</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The days of the internal combustion engine in Bentley cars are numbered. As part of its strategy, the British luxury brand plans to sell only electric cars and plug-in hybrids by 2026, and four years later become a brand that produces only electric cars. Indeed, the methodical electrification of its line is already in full swing, and the Bentley Bentayga became the first Bentley equipped with a plug-in hybrid powerplant. The next one will be the 2022 Bentley Flying Spur hybrid, which will also receive a plug-in hybrid variant, which brings it closer to the Flying Spur with a V-8 engine in power.<br>There are few places in the world that go well with the Flying Spur hybrid, but Beverly Hills, with its luxurious lifestyle, eco-friendly mentality and impressive roads, has become the perfect place to experience this electrified horse. We spent the whole day driving from the city center to the picturesque canyons surrounding Ojai and back, conducting a test drive. Let\'s not hide it, we really enjoyed driving such a car.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>The Smallest Details Of \"Flying Spur\"</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Equipped with a 2.9-liter twin-turbocharged V-6 engine and a 100—kilowatt electric motor located between the engine and transmission, the Flying Spur hybrid delivers 536 hp and 553 Nm of torque - this is only slightly less than the 542 hp and 568 Nm of the V-8 model. Its rechargeable battery with a capacity of 18.0 kWh (the total battery capacity is 18.9 kWh, while 18 kWh can be used) allows the four-door sedan to drive about 40 kilometers in EV (electric vehicle) mode, according to Bentley, and it takes about two and a half hours, which is a relatively fast period of time. These figures should appeal to many, the range gives them a sufficient range for daily trips, while there will always be a full gas tank at their disposal, in case of need. An eight-speed dual-clutch automatic transmission provides power transmission to all four wheels via the standard Flying Spur Hybrid all-wheel drive system.<br>As you would expect from a car of this class and price category, the cabin is quiet and calm at speed. Riding is similar to sliding, except that there is a connection between the driver and the vehicle. Almost all potholes, pits and irregularities were carefully eliminated by the suspension on double wishbones in front and the multi-link system in the rear. The main characteristics of the Flying Spur hybrid are complemented by a three-chamber pneumatic and spring suspension, which further enhances its ride quality while keeping its dynamic behavior competitive.<br>During operation, the driver can choose one of three hybrid configurations — EV mode, in which the car runs exclusively on electricity, Hybrid mode, in which the battery and engine work together, and energy saving mode, which balances the operation of the engine and electric motor for maximum battery energy savings, for later use.<br>The Flying Spur hybrid wouldn\'t be a Bentley if it didn\'t have an increased attention to detail, which is immediately felt when landing inside. Simply put, it is an outstanding skill. Our Jetstream Blue model, finished inside with blue leather and red contrasting stitching, which gave the cabin a feeling of youth and brightness: the leather and cushioning of the seats seem perfectly soft. The use of metal in the decoration is noticeable, it does not overload with a sparkling excess. Rather, the widespread use of massive wooden elements in the decoration around the perimeter attracts attention.<br>There is nothing in the cabin that immediately signals the ownership of the Flying Spur Volkswagen Group hybrid. Those with an eagle eye will notice that the Porsche infotainment system is used, but each button, the choice of materials and air vents are unique for this particular Bentley.<br>As with any Flying Spur, the rear seats are the best in the cabin. In addition to the large head and foot space, those in the back can enjoy the massage seats and choose their own configurations using a smartphone-style device that is neatly positioned on the center console, and from it you can adjust the temperature, ambient lighting and control music. Of course, the rear seats recline, and a soft pillow supports the neck and head so that you can relax.<br>If there is a desire to get behind the wheel, the front seats also do not lag behind. Both the driver and the front passenger also have massage seats, and more than enough space is available to them.<br>The car looks very good! After all, the 2022 Bentley Flying Spur hybrid doesn\'t sacrifice performance, ride quality or luxury for fuel economy. An approach has been used that bodes well for Bentley as the company begins the hard work of transforming itself for the upcoming electrification.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Review of the Bentley Flying Spur Hybrid 2022', 'This is the second Bentley model to receive a plug-in hybrid powertrain, and the trend towards hybridization will certainly continue.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'review-of-the-bentley-flying-spur-hybrid-2022', '', '', '2022-11-19 16:32:46', '2022-11-19 13:32:46', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=633', 0, 'post', '', 0),
