(637, 2, '2022-11-19 16:41:12', '2022-11-19 13:41:12', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Many automakers have tried to create a supercar that you can drive every day without much compromise. And these efforts, whether developing a bodywork or adapting an existing car, have rarely been successful. After 14 months behind the wheel of the Chevrolet Corvette Z51 of 2021 — our 2020 car, the feeling is not as enthusiastic as it was originally.<br>Yes, we\'re still going to stand our ground and say that the Corvette is the only car that everyone needs. Within reasonable limits, of course. People with children or those who regularly transport plywood will need another set of wheels. Everyone else? Get it, sign up…<br>You see, we\'ve done everything we could think of with this Corvette. Eight hundred kilometer road trips? — Several times. Bring home a Christmas tree? — Tied to the roof. Off-road? — Once Google Maps sent us on a short way, which turned out to be a dirt road in poor condition, and we still got there without damage. A home appliance store? — Done. Buying groceries? — Every week. Beat the Porsche Cayman GT4 on the race track? — Yes, no problem. And all this costs almost $47,000 less.<br>We were able to do all this because the Corvette is really practical and has excellent performance. With two trunks and a removable roof, transporting most things home was not a big problem. No one took all this on vacation: we just packed a few hand bags instead of one big one.<br>Regardless of whether we were driving down the street or one navigator knows where, the combination of the C8 with best-in-class driving qualities, extremely comfortable sports seats and stability at high speed made a trip of any length easy. Tuned to \"My Mode\" — a customizable mode with improved braking sensation, loud exhaust, soft suspension settings and light steering — the car is absolutely comfortable.<br>Sometimes I had to slow down because of big bumps, whether it was on a dirt road or at the entrance to my own steep driveway. In the latter case, we set up the automatic lifting of the front suspension of the car by GPS tag, and this action is an absolute necessity. We stopped taking any risks at all and just raised our nose whenever the roadway, speed bump or something else looked like we could leave our bumper here. Labeling all the places in our neighborhoods and around the office has made commuting a lot less stressful.<br>The car also copes very well with the tasks of the Corvette. For example, put the Cayman GT4 in place. Or accelerate to 100 km/h per hour in just 2.8 seconds and make cars with significantly more power and thicker characteristics blush.<br>True, tires with high-speed dynamic driving on roads teeming with turns wore out in less than 16,000 km, but it was worth it. The new kit costs $1,889.96 for tires and $100 for mounting and balancing. Maintenance of supercars is not cheap.<br>By comparison, the Corvette is available for repair. One visit to the service center, for which we paid, cost us only $ 183, which is significantly less than the average luxury car service takes (usually more than $ 200 per visit), although much more than our 2015 Chevrolet Corvette Z51 C7 cost, which was serviced for free for the first few years and did not require attachments. It so happened that the front trunk stopped opening around the time the car was in service, which required ordering a new opener and returning after 12 days to install it, but this was covered by the warranty along with a couple of minor reviews. Our C7 Corvette was a little more problematic than our C8.<br>Although nothing else required repairs, we have a few suggestions for Chevrolet when the mid-cycle update arrives. While we don\'t hate the long row of buttons on the center console, as some do, we agree that ergonomics just isn\'t there, and it creates a wall that the passenger can\'t reach through. While Chevy is rebuilding it all, it can also move the wireless phone charger from behind the elbow to a more convenient location. A set of hooks on the ceiling behind the seats, to hang a jacket, also does not hurt. Anyway, we can\'t see anything from the back window. Additional thermal insulation in the rear trunk would also be not superfluous. Cold food is always stored in the front trunk.<br>It would be great if Chevy could find a way to prevent rainwater from getting on the hood and trunk lid into the front and rear trunks when they are opened. It would also be nice if they could reduce the decorative side blades. They are installed in the widest parts of the door and primarily hit a car parked nearby. Eliminating them would make it easier to squeeze through the door when someone parks too close.<br>In general, these are small fixes that could please us, but they are unlikely to significantly affect the choice. Thoughtful features, such as the front hood hidden under the headlight, front cameras pointing down, automatic comfortable entry/exit functions, make us forget about most of our problems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Chevrolet Corvette Z51 2021 Annual Test Drive', 'Many automakers have tried to create a supercar that you can drive every day without much compromise. And these efforts, whether developing a bodywork or adapting an existing car, have rarely been ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'chevrolet-corvette-z51-2021-annual-test-drive', '', '', '2022-11-19 16:41:12', '2022-11-19 13:41:12', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=637', 0, 'post', '', 0),
