(640, 2, '2022-11-19 16:46:16', '2022-11-19 13:46:16', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Throughout the history of Chevrolet, the expansion of the Rallye Sport (or RS) brand has always, in fact, been an appearance package, but it was used on cars that at least had decent characteristics. The RS expansion began to appear too often in the automaker\'s offerings, which made it a little cheaper: the appearance of the Chevrolet Equinox RS 2022 really demonstrated how disappointing it can be. Of course, we got a clearer body and all-wheel drive, but what is a 1.5-liter turbocharged I-4 engine and a less sporty six-speed automatic transmission?! Although the small crossover SUV is easy to drive, as befits a modern car, the engine and transmission evoke memories of turbo lag and long shifts, which we clearly do not expect today.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>What is good?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Let\'s start with the positives of the 2022 Chevrolet Equinox RS, because if you ignore the weak engine and the six—speed gearbox with slow shifts, the Equinox is a competent little SUV. It has plenty of space for passengers, comfortable seats and decent standard equipment. Outside, LED lighting is everywhere, including headlights plus an electric trunk door. Nineteen-inch aluminum wheels are included in the RS package. Also visually distinguished are the black roof rails, window frames, badges, as well as the unique RS radiator grille. Combining all this with the cherry-red paint worn by our test car, the Equinox becomes a beautiful car. The interior is still made in the Equinox style, but it has RS elements, such as a leather-covered steering wheel, a gearshift switch with the inscription \"RS\" in red and contrasting red stitching.<br>Our 2022 Chevrolet Equinox RS test car boasted an additional RS leather package that includes a Bose premium system with seven speakers and black RS leather seats (with red stitching), as well as an additional infotainment package that includes heated steering wheel, USB ports for data transfer on the center console, as well as a 220-volt outlet. It also included the 3 Plus infotainment package, which features an 8.0-inch high-definition touchscreen with functionality for CarPlay and Android Auto apps. In addition, the advanced security package included a 360 HD camera, heated exterior mirrors and adaptive cruise control. Everything that is in these packages cannot be overlooked, especially the three-dimensional view system, which greatly simplifies parking. We get not only front and rear cameras, but also a top-down view that makes sure we don\'t park too close to other cars or the curb.<br>The only oddity was the adaptive cruise control, which worked well most of the time. But sometimes he behaved aggressively and followed other cars too close, even when the maximum follow interval was dialed. In other cases, he decided to be insufficiently aggressive when he was set to the closest possible distance of the distance. It seemed to do best with taller vehicles such as trucks, large trucks, and mid-size SUVs: it lagged much more when dealing with something smaller than a mid-size sedan.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>What indicators are known?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>From the spot, the Chevrolet Equinox RS 2022 did not gain momentum above 2500 rpm, and its long first gear of 4.58:1 seemed to last forever. Gear shifting started to happen a little faster after the first gear was turned off, but we showed the best acceleration time from a standstill to 100 km/h in just 8.9 seconds.<br>Then the consumption of gasoline Equinox RS is known: 9,4/7,8/8,7 l / 100 km of mileage in the city / highway / in a mixed cycle. These numbers are slightly behind compared to the 2022 Honda CR-V AWD and the 2022 Toyota RAV4 AWD. The CR-V is also equipped with a 1.5-liter turbocharged engine, but produces 8,7/7,3/8,4 l/100 km. Chevy\'s six-speed automatic just doesn\'t fit its engine, while Honda uses a CVT and the RAV4 gets two extra gears (it comes with an eight-speed automatic). The two competitors also reach speeds from a standstill to 100 km/h in the case of the RAV4 in 8.0 seconds, and the CR-V in 7.8 seconds.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Reasonable manageability</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When driving at night, Equinox gives confidence not only with its handling, but also with the overview it provides, since LED headlights give a wide view forward and sideways on sharp turns. Its automatic high beam also works great and can distinguish between the brightest driveway and house lights, compared to car headlights. It\'s all fun until you have to stop or get out of an aggressively steep turn — if you let the engine drop below 2500 rpm, the turbocharging lags behind, and the gearbox doesn\'t shift aggressively enough to get the four-cylinder engine out of the dead zone.<br>However, let\'s forget about the engine and transmission. Even more disappointing is the limited cargo space of Equinox. With the rear seats raised, we have only 0.8 cubic meters of cargo space, which is not much. To transport a 20x24x24 box unfolded, we had to lower the rear seats to get another 0.9 cubic meters (only 2 cubic meters when the seats are lowered). But the main all-wheel drive competitors Chevrolet Equinox offer a large capacity with folded seats.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Is it worth buying it?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Overall, the 2022 Chevrolet Equinox RS AWD is an excellent crossover SUV that is held back by a small but demanding and slow engine, a slow transmission and a relatively small cargo space. Yes, it provides driving pleasure, but that doesn\'t put it above the Honda CR-V AWD and Toyota RAV4 AWD.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Chevrolet Equinox RS 2022 Test Drive', 'Throughout the history of Chevrolet, the expansion of the Rallye Sport (or RS) brand has always, in fact, been an appearance package, but it was used on cars that at least had decent characteristics.', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'chevrolet-equinox-rs-2022-test-drive', '', '', '2022-11-19 16:46:16', '2022-11-19 13:46:16', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=640', 0, 'post', '', 0),
