(643, 2, '2022-11-19 16:51:14', '2022-11-19 13:51:14', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the battle to determine which automaker has the biggest pickups, Chevrolet\'s latest model needs another 280 horsepower and a wider track to match the largest pair of Ford and Ram. This is a real difference that can be seen. The sand-throwing Chevrolet Silverado 1500 ZR2 of 2023 looks ordinary when parked next to a Ford F-150 Raptor R or Ram 1500 TRX. No wings stuffed with creatine. No whopping 37-inch tires. No advertising stickers.<br>However, this is not a reason to write off the Silverado ZR2. We can say that the ZR2 is a sleeping car, which is much better in operation than it seems. Getting behind the wheel, you can quickly discover that this pickup has great capabilities and it can withstand dirt and sand.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>A miracle with a large volume</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Chevrolet\'s $71,895 off-road flagship is equipped with the same powerful 6.2-liter V-8 engine, which is also available in Silverado on top trim trim levels such as High-falutin, High Country. The engine with a large displacement has the manners corresponding to a luxury car with the motivation to actively use performance. A smart 10-speed automatic selects the right gears at the right moments, which means that the engine with 420 horsepower and a torque of 623 Nm is always ready. If you look for any complaints, then this engine can be called \"too civilized\" for such a wild truck. Even at full throttle, the exhaust sound of the ZR2 is a muffled hum, not a primal roar.<br>The 2625-kilogram ZR2 accelerates to 100 km/h in 6.1 seconds and overcomes the 400-meter mark in 14.6 seconds at a speed of 153 km/h before the speedometer needle crashes into the 160 km/h electronic speed limiter. The Raptor with a 450-horsepower Ford twin-turbocharged V-6 engine accelerates to 100 km/h 0.5 seconds faster, and the Ram 1500 Rebel with a 395-horsepower Hemi V-8 engine requires an additional 0.3 seconds. The TRX (and presumably the Raptor R, which we haven\'t tested yet) is in a different league.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>The right balance of softness and hardness</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Without the 700-plus horsepower of the V-8, the main attraction of the ZR2 is a set of four perfectly tuned multimatic slide valves. Compared to the prefabricated elements in conventional shock absorbers, spool valves provide engineers with more precise control of damping characteristics and more stable operation throughout the entire service life of the pickup. Each ZR2 shock absorber pushes fluid through one of the three valve housings, depending on the position of the wheel.<br>The Chevrolet ZR2 takes a purist approach to off-road driving. It finds traction by locking the front and rear differentials and a transfer case that offers 2 modes High, Auto, 4 modes High and 4 modes Low. 33-inch BF Goodrich Wrangler Territory MT tires are the largest that the Silverado body allows, do not need traction. They just grab the ground and push the Silverado forward. It is noteworthy that the car does not have a stabilizer bar, programmable damper settings and active exhaust. Due to the small number of adjustable elements, in addition to the default Tour setting, there are only two driving modes, generally useless. However, these are not complaints. It\'s nice to drive a modern, productive car in 2022 and not be distracted by a lot of inconvenient settings that trivially affect the driving experience.<br>More surprising than the ZR2\'s off-road abilities is its sophistication on the road. On asphalt, these shock absorbers with slide valves provide excellent control over the body. Stable riding softens the roll of the body without causing sudden shocks. In turns and on uneven asphalt, the ZR2\'s movements are surprisingly neat for a three-ton truck that can instantly lose control. This is partly due to the rigidity of the structure, which can really be felt. Or maybe, more precisely, it is impossible to feel the same design flaws that exist in other pickups. The Ford F-150 shakes and bends harder than the Silverado, although this is often well masked by the Raptor\'s soft suspension. Silverado\'s wide skill set is a credit to Chevrolet engineers to the same extent as the Multimatic damper technology.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>The pickup is larger than the width of its track</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Compared to other pick-up caricatures, where cars conquer dunes and jump from hills, the Silverado ZR2 looks like a cartoon with underlined irregular features. His narrow shoulders and (relatively) small tires seem out of proportion to his angry face and high cross-country ability. We would really like the designers and engineers of Chevrolet to have freedom of action and create a ZR2 that would match the clumsiest Ford and Ram trucks, but the ZR2 that we got is worth loving for what it is. While it may not have the reputation of a Raptor or TRX, the Silverado ZR2 has SUV capabilities that are much, much wider than its track width.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Chevrolet Silverado 1500 ZR2 2022 Test Drive: Who is hiding in the shadow of giants', 'In the battle to determine which automaker has the biggest pickups, Chevrolet\'s latest model needs another 280 horsepower and a wider track to match the largest pair of Ford and Ram. This is a real ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'chevrolet-silverado-1500-zr2-2022-test-drive-who-is-hiding-in-the-shadow-of-giants', '', '', '2022-11-19 16:51:14', '2022-11-19 13:51:14', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=643', 0, 'post', '', 0),
