(646, 2, '2022-11-19 16:58:35', '2022-11-19 13:58:35', '<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Due to the fact that its compact crossover counterparts are selling well, Ford is honing the Escape style and upgrading its electric architecture</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Few cars using the same basic platform differ from each other more than the square Bronco Sport SUV based on the Ford C2 and the diamond-shaped Escape with urban equipment. If they looked more similar, the first one could negate the sales of the second one. Both models are sold at or close to the level already three years after the release of the fourth-generation Escape model, so Ford is weighing down the appearance and behavior of the somewhat mild 2020 Escape.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Fresh appearance</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Among the main visual changes is a bolder new hood, which is located on top of a deeper sculptural grille, framed by a pair of \"four-eyed\" headlights with LED illumination, which look much more expressive (also in the style of BMW\'s skosh). At the upper trim levels, a so-called LED strip connects these DRL headlights, illuminating the gap between the hood and the radiator grille. A new front panel with an artificial overlay completes a more spectacular makeup. Other exterior changes are minimal: new 17-, 18- and 19-inch wheels, new LED taillights, rear panel trim and moving the hatch cover from below over the license plate.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>New finishing of the ST line</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Another confirmation that Escape has become the leader of the Ford C2 compact crossover line on the platform is the new ST Line package, which obscures the entire main trim — the radiator grille, moldings around the perimeter of the windows, a large rear spoiler with one wing, etc. Even 19-inch wheels turn black on top models. ST Line\'s off-road ambitions are further downplayed by the body-colored wheel arch moldings instead of dark gray. Inside there are accents in the form of red stitching and a steering wheel with a flat bottom, although the seat material varies depending on the trim level. The least expensive 1.5-liter Escape ST line starts at a price of $31,335. The ST Line Select and Elite models have everything that corresponds to other levels of equipment. Ford expects that half of all buyers will choose the ST Line.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Other levels of equipment and prices</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Meaningless trim names such as S, SE and SEL have disappeared in favor of base, Active and Platinum. This is a basic configuration with a level of configuration bracketing, which offers several packages of options to adapt Escape to the specific wishes of customers. The base Escape starts at $28,995, the Active (which doesn\'t get a special badge) costs $32,210, and the Platinum is $37,515 with a standard 2.0-liter transmission with all-wheel drive: a regular hybrid transmission with front or all-wheel drive is optional. The front-wheel drive hybrid Escape with plug-in leads the line as a fully loaded package at a price of $39,995.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Power units</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The 2023 Ford Escape continues to offer two petrol and two hybrid models with performance that seems virtually unchanged on paper. But both the 1.5-liter turbocharged EcoBoost three-cylinder engine and the 2.0—liter EcoBoost turbo four-cylinder engine are fundamentally new engines, redesigned in accordance with stricter emission standards. Hybrid and plug-in hybrid models use the same 2.5-liter four-cylinder engine with an Atkinson cycle, with some minor changes in output characteristics due to a new measurement method for this complex installation with a gasoline engine/two motor generators. The eight-speed automatic transmission (EcoBoost) and the planetary variator (hybrids) have not changed, as has the optional all-wheel drive system. PHEV offers four electric vehicle modes: Auto, EV Now, EV Later and EV Charge with the maximum possible fully electric speed of 136 km/h.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>New electrical architecture</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ford\'s latest electric architecture, first introduced on the Mustang Mach E and future trucks, brings new functionality to Escape, including the Sync 4 infotainment package fully connected to the cloud, Ford Co-Pilot 360 safety technology with an intersection and blind spot assistance system, lane keeping assistance system, a cross-traffic detection system, braking assistance system, built-in voice commands \"OK, Ford\" and Alexa (with a free three-year subscription), as well as navigation. Perhaps more important is the ability of the new architecture to receive updates over the air to improve current features or add new features. The 2023 Ford Escape will also receive upgraded screens: previously optional cluster and center screens will become standard, and the largest center screen will increase from 8.0 to 13.2 inches. All screens can be reconfigured, and the enlarged central screen combines all the controls of the air conditioning system into a series of digital buttons that always remain visible at the bottom of the screen (basic and low-level control panels with an 8.0-inch screen retain the physical buttons for controlling the air conditioning system just below the screen).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Is it worth waiting for the Ford Escape of 2023?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With a price difference of only about $315, the improved electrical architecture alone is worth choosing a model of the 23rd year of release. The ST Line style update and appearance package look much better, and the larger screen and smaller dashboard are all worthy upgrades. These mid-cycle changes should help Ford\'s fourth bestseller continue to sell strongly when it hits the market in early 2023. However, it seems that the updates do not take into account our main complaints about poor-quality interior materials, an unsatisfactory base engine or an unsupportive driver\'s seat, so we would like to conduct a comparative test of this highly competitive class next year as soon as possible.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'A First Look at the Ford Escape of 2023', 'Few cars using the same basic platform differ from each other more than the square Bronco Sport SUV based on the Ford C2 and the diamond-shaped Escape with urban equipment. If they looked more', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-first-look-at-the-ford-escape-of-2023', '', '', '2022-11-19 16:58:35', '2022-11-19 13:58:35', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=646', 0, 'post', '', 0),
