(649, 2, '2022-11-19 17:04:18', '2022-11-19 14:04:18', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By creating the 2024 Mustang, Ford has taken a bold and potentially historic step. The seventh generation Mustang is probably the last one running on hydrocarbon fuel. According to rumors, Chevrolet is going to replace the Camaro as we know it, before the final transition to electric traction in 2024. Dodge has confirmed that its Challenger and Charger will offer electric traction around the same time. A passionate project in the truest sense of the word, the Mustang 2024 team needed to justify the use of internal combustion engines on a muscle car at every step, even if the management ultimately supported its actions. After all, Ford is in the process of mastering electric trucks and SUVs.<br>Mustang enthusiasts, who have purchased about 10 million cars since production began in 1964, should rejoice at the fact that Ford uses internal combustion engines even at a time when its main competitors are leaving the segment of muscle cars with a gasoline engine, and sales of coupes and convertibles continue to decline, while sedans (not SUVs) and pickups are becoming an endangered species, being supplanted by increasingly popular high-traffic vehicles. Think about it: The Mustang is even today the only car Ford sells in North America. The Mustang Mach-E electric crossover is already superior to the traditional Mustang coupe.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Ford Mustang and GT 2024 are still offered in coupe and convertible bodies</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When the 2024 Ford Mustang goes on sale early next summer, consumers will still be able to choose between a coupe and a convertible, as well as between a base model with an EcoBoost four-cylinder engine or a more powerful GT with a V-8, which also comes with a manual transmission. Over the long life cycle, we expect names like Boss, Bullitt and Mach 1 to appear. \"There is certainly room for more in this platform architecture and powertrains,\" says Mustang chief engineer Ed Krenz.<br>The new S650 platform is a modified version of the existing S550 with some details such as the roof, front pillar and rear window. Ideas of hybridizing the Mustang or adding all-wheel drive were discarded. Ford designers have carefully honed the look, which is as evolutionary as the new S650. The result is instantly recognizable as a Mustang and meets all the requirements thanks to the long hood, short tailgate and tapering roof.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Mustang Styling</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Early designs were discarded in favor of a bolder look with muscular wings, a lower waistline and a sexier fit. \"He looks like a fist in the wind walking down the road,\" said global design director Joel Piaskowski.<br>If the sixth-generation Mustang has become more international, the seventh generation returns to its American roots, providing a modern interpretation of the classics: new three-lane headlights with LED lighting to match the taillights and spectacular rear corners that reduce and act as a spoiler, making the car wider, although the proportions have not changed much.<br>For the first time, the Mustang EcoBoost has a completely unique front end design compared to the GT. The changes go beyond individual inserts in the radiator grille. The lower grille openings, which are fake on a regular Mustang, are larger on the GT, one side is closed to the air flow, and the other is fully functional. The air also exits through the hood from the glossy black hood of the GT.<br>The roof line was designed so that drivers could get in and out without removing their helmet on the track. The convertible has a insulated fabric roof with a latch with a single handle and a button for opening and closing with one click.<br>Among the 11 colors on offer are two new colors: Splash Yellow and Vapor Blue, as well as new colors for stripes, Brembo brake calipers and seat belts. A number of appearance packages allow you to further customize the appearance. Wheel sizes range from standard 17-inch to 19-inch on the GT, with optional 20-inch wheels.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Impressive new Mustang interior</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Interior design manager Ricardo Garcia says it\'s time to shake up the interior, and he\'s ready to get customer feedback on the ideas expressed by the team, which over a three-year period turned into a new, more open cockpit.<br>A new flat-bottom steering wheel is included as standard: it\'s nice to hold in your hands. The Sync4-based infotainment system has fewer physical buttons because most functions can be controlled from the screen. There is a 12.4-inch display directly in front of the driver and a 13.2-inch center screen located at an angle to the driver. The graphics are clear and varied, and it changes depending on the selected driving mode.<br>Finally, there is a multimedia storage with a flat wireless charging pad, USB ports and a slanted phone slot. The upgraded seats are covered with fabric, synthetic or genuine leather, and the interior has a carbon fiber finish. The top—end audio system is Bang &amp; Olufsen, and the Mustang is compatible with Apple CarPlay and Android Auto, with built-in Amazon Alexa for voice commands.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Mustang Powertrain Upgrades</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The turbocharged base 2.3-liter EcoBoost I-4 has been updated to reduce emissions and improve fuel efficiency. We don\'t have the specifications yet, but the engineers say that the power won\'t drop, which means that it should continue to produce at least 310 hp and 474 Nm of torque. This fourth-generation powerplant is known as the MPC engine (modular Powertrain) and it will make its debut on the Mustang. There is also a 2.0-liter MPC that will run on the 2023 Lincoln Corsair and the 2023 Ford Escape.<br>The 5.0-liter Coyote V-8 engine is on its fourth update and is also installed in the 2022 Ford F-150 pickup truck with the option to turn off the cylinders for better fuel economy. The engineers didn\'t want to use this fuel economy system for the Mustang because it makes the engine too tall, degrading the trim and hood height, and also reduces engine power. For the Mustang, the upgraded V-8 is equipped with a new steel oil pan and a double air intake. A double air intake with a throttle valve will double the air flow to create the most powerful GT to date. This means that it surpasses today\'s 450 hp and 569 Nm. The car is still equipped with an active exhaust with the Mustang\'s signature sound, but adds a quiet mode to make the neighbors happy. GT owners get a Getrag six-speed manual transmission with rev adjustment, or they can opt for an improved 10-speed automatic.<br>The kit also includes large brake discs and calipers. Engineers say the steering is noticeably more precise thanks to the new rack and faster gear ratio, and MagneRide\'s excellent electronic adaptive shock absorbers have been tuned for the new car and will be available with the performance package.<br>There are a couple of unique features that will delight buyers, starting with the new electronic drift brake developed with the help of professional drifter Vaughn Gittin Jr. It usually behaves like a regular electric parking brake until the driver activates the \"drift brake\" mode, which disables traction (you can choose traction off or advanced traction off). Then pressing this brake causes the ABS module to hydraulically actuate only the rear brakes in proportion to the movement of the brake handle.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'The first look of the Ford Mustang 2024: photos and full information', 'By creating the 2024 Mustang, Ford has taken a bold and potentially historic step. The seventh generation Mustang is probably the last one running on hydrocarbon fuel. According to rumors, Chevrolet is going ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-first-look-of-the-ford-mustang-2024-photos-and-full-information', '', '', '2022-11-19 17:04:18', '2022-11-19 14:04:18', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=649', 0, 'post', '', 0),
