(652, 2, '2022-11-19 17:09:51', '2022-11-19 14:09:51', '<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Here it is… A pickup truck with serious power under the hood and an impressive appearance</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Since the Ford Ranger of the current generation appeared on the market a few years ago, we have looked with some envy at the world-famous Ranger Raptor, which has swollen wings, large ground clearance and a twin-turbocharged diesel engine with a torque of 369 Nm. But then the Ford Ranger Raptor model 2023 appeared, and now we have something to compare with.<br>Firstly, the 2.0-liter inline four-cylinder turbocharged diesel engine of previous versions disappeared, and in its place appeared a 3.0-liter V6 with dual turbocharging, modified by Ford Performance. In European countries, the truck will develop a power of 284 horsepower and a torque of 362 Nm — impressive, of course. But it\'s just a pony, compared to the Australian version, developing a whopping 392 hp and 430 Nm. And this is most likely a version that will be sold only in the USA, although Ford is not talking about American specifications yet. This high-performance engine is equipped with a delay protection system similar to the one installed on the Focus ST for the European market. Power is transmitted through the familiar Ford 10-speed automatic and a standard all-wheel drive system with a two-speed transfer case.<br>The off-road equipment of the car is also impressive. There are the necessary front and rear differentials, as well as a full set of selectable terrain modes, including Baja mode for high-speed desert racing. By the way, the chassis was reinforced in all the expected ways to cope with serious loads on the suspension, for example, when colliding with a medium-sized stone at a speed of 100 km/h on the beach. All suspension fasteners are reinforced, as are some parts of the frame, in particular around the spare wheel. We can show all the reinforcements in the image below, and they are no different from those installed in the 2022 Ford Bronco Raptor, which uses a similar frame.<br>The suspension itself consists of powerful aluminum levers at the front and a movable axle with a Watt lever at the rear. Ford used 2.5-inch internal bypass shock absorbers with an active valve so that the suspension could cope with wheel vibrations. (Interestingly, these devices have a smaller diameter than the 3.1-inch devices in the Bronco Raptor.) Ford says the Teflon-containing oil inside these revised shock absorbers reduces friction and performance-reducing heat by 50 percent. Ford also promises better comfort when driving on the road than the previous model could offer.<br>Serious protective armor is installed on the bottom of the pickup truck: 2.3 mm thick steel plates protect vulnerable areas under the front of the truck, and also protrude from under the bumper, giving the truck a stylish bite. The radiator, steering, engine pan and differential are protected.<br>The most important thing is that the new Raptor Ranger manages to maintain the beautiful appearance of an \"ordinary\" ranger of the next generation, who has just received a serious dose of adrenaline. And it is worth noting that the American Ranger of the current generation was not originally developed for the American market — it was adapted after the fact as a truck for the world market. And it\'s noticeable. The new Ranger is a real global product developed jointly with the USA. The new Ranger Raptor shows that serious thoughtful work has been done to ensure that customers like it, who have very different ideas about what a pickup truck should be. All the elements that we would expect to see are present — large wings with black arches, a radiator grille with the FORD logo, which seems to be visible from space, as well as a sturdy rear end with rolled-up forked exhaust pipes.<br>The interior is much more modern than the current Ranger, and obviously the new car is very similar to the global Ranger we saw last year, with the Raptor\'s expected touches — bright orange accents, a sporty steering wheel and reinforced sports seats.<br>Now is the right time to mention that in the photo we are showing the ROW version, in particular the version for the UK market. Don\'t be surprised if there are minor differences in the American or European (in countries with \"left\" steering) markets — front and rear lights and bumpers often differ in different countries.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'First Look at the Ford Ranger Raptor 2023', 'Since the Ford Ranger of the current generation appeared on the market a few years ago, we have looked with some envy at the world-famous Ranger Raptor, which has swollen wings, large ground clearance and', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'first-look-at-the-ford-ranger-raptor-2023', '', '', '2022-11-19 17:09:51', '2022-11-19 14:09:51', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=652', 0, 'post', '', 0),
