(658, 2, '2022-11-19 18:46:23', '2022-11-19 15:46:23', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Imagine a high-performance Lamborghini Urus, which weighs several kilograms, and you get Urus S</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Fans of Zack Snyder\'s 2013 superhero blockbuster \"Man of Steel\" may think that the new nickname \"S\", added to the new base of the Lamborghini Urus S 2023, means \"hope\", because that\'s what Superman tells Lois Lane about the meaning of the symbol on the chest of his suit in that movie. Hope would be appropriate, given the financial security provided by the 20,000 Urus models already sold over the past few years. But I bet that for Lamborghini, the \"S\" actually means \"Super\", given how much they like to call the updated model a \"super SUV with the perfect lifestyle.\" There is nothing shameful in claiming such a title with this car, unlike another Italian supercar brand Ferrari and its new Purosangue — a hatchback for a family lifestyle, which they refuse to call an SUV.<br>At the same time, the Lamborghini Urus S is equipped with a twin-turbocharged V-8 engine, which in most markets still produces 666 horsepower (the marginal notes explain that in China the power will be limited to 640 hp), and a torque of 850 Nm associated with an eight-speed automatic transmission and all-wheel drive. Lamborghini also says that the S and Performante have the same transmission calibration. So what is really the difference between them?<br>Well, the Performante is still a lighter SUV with a claimed weight savings of about 47 kilograms, which is mainly achieved by replacing a large number of body panels and interior parts with similar carbon fiber, as well as the use of a titanium exhaust system and lightweight wheels. (How much do the rear seats weigh in the S? Are they really necessary?) However, the difference in acceleration rates between the two new SUVs is barely discernible: According to Lamborghini, the Performante accelerates from 0 to 100 km/h in 3.3 seconds, and the new S takes a little more time by 3.5 seconds. Both the S and the Performante are designed for a fuel consumption of 14.1 l/ 100 km in the European WLTP test cycle.<br>The Urus S will also receive a very similar, if not identical, design update as the Performante, with updated front and rear bumpers, a new black trim, a lightweight ventilated carbon fiber hood, a twin-tube exhaust system and new wheels from 21 to 23 inches. The exterior trim can be made in glossy or matte black and carbon fiber, there is an additional carbon fiber roof, and now there are more color options, trim, wheels, trim and parts than ever before.<br>The adjustable air suspension system seems to be preserved, but there is also a new engine sound that is now sharper in every driving mode. Inside, the Urus S offers completely new color and finishing solutions, including two new two-tone Sportivos and refined styling. In Europe, the Urus S costs from 195,538 euros before taxes, or about 191,197 dollars at the current exchange rate, although prices may vary.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'First Look of Lamborghini Urus 2023: Now everything is super', 'Fans of Zack Snyder\'s 2013 superhero blockbuster \"Man of Steel\" may think that the new nickname \"S\", added to the new base of the Lamborghini Urus S 2023, means \"hope\", because that\'s what Superman', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'first-look-of-lamborghini-urus-2023-now-everything-is-super', '', '', '2022-11-19 18:46:23', '2022-11-19 15:46:23', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=658', 0, 'post', '', 0),
