(670, 2, '2022-11-19 19:03:25', '2022-11-19 16:03:25', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The magic of modern automotive mathematics: the Mercedes-AMG C43 engine of 2023, the entry-level Mercedes C-Class line, produces almost 5 percent more power than the one that powered the previous C43. The C43 sedan is the first version of the AMG W206 C-Class model, released in 2021. This is a warm rather than hot AMG sedan, focused, according to Mercedes-Benz USA, on competing with the BMW M 340 i xDrive and Audi S4, rather than with the full-size M3 sedan and RS5 Sportback models. A more powerful C63 is coming, which is designed to take care of these two.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>AMG Formula</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Visually, the new C43 follows the proven AMG formula. Compared to the regular C-Class, the exterior of the C43 features more aggressive styling elements, including a menacing AMG grille with vertical lines, unique wheels (18-inch wheels will be standard for cars with American specifications, available in 19 and 20 inches), quad exhaust pipes and a spoiler on the trunk lid. Hot tip: On larger wheels, the C43 will go faster, as the maximum speed increases from 249 km/h to 265 km/h, compared to standard 18-inch liski.<br>Inside are new, lighter AMG sports seats, a carbon fiber stripe on the dashboard and lots of MB-Tex faux leather with microfiber lining and contrast stitching. And since this is an AMG car from the 2020s, both the digital dashboard and the central screen of the infotainment system offer AMG-specific graphics options. Steering wheel from EQ with touch switches and controls on four horizontal spokes.<br>The chassis improvements are also in line with familiar AMG practice. The C43 retains the steel springs of the conventional C-class, but the body movements are controlled by adaptive AMG shock absorbers, which offer three damping schemes — Comfort, Sport and Sport +, each of which constantly adapts to the condition of the road surface and driving style.<br>The steering knuckles and suspension hinges have been redesigned on the front axle. The multi-link rear axle is equipped with stiffer bushings, and the front spacer and aluminum panel under the engine compartment help to increase the rigidity of the body by 5 percent.<br>Steering on the rear wheels is standard, the wheels turn 2.5 degrees in the opposite direction from the front wheels to increase maneuverability at speeds below 60 km/h and 0.7 degrees in the same direction as the front wheels at higher speeds to increase stability. The brake discs are steel, 14.6-inch front and 12.6-inch rear.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Engine</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, the big news is what\'s under the hood. The C43 2023 is the first Mercedes sedan with a longitudinally mounted four—cylinder engine, starting with the 190E 2.5-16 model, sold from 1989 to 1993. The new engine is a slightly hybridized version of the 2.0-liter turbocharged inline-four engine used in American versions of the GLA and GLB SUVs, as well as the CLA four-door coupe.<br>The engine code-named M139L—L for \"longitudinal\" is an engine made by hand in Affalterbach using AMG technology \"one person, one engine\", develops 402 horsepower at 6750 rpm and a torque of 500 Nm at 5000 rpm, and a 48-volt starter-generator with belt drive provides if necessary, a temporary increase in power by 13 hp. The main technology of the M139L is an electric turbocharger from exhaust gases, which uses an 8-horsepower brushless DC electric motor with permanent magnets to control the speed of the shaft on which the turbine and compressor are installed.<br>Simply put, the 1.6-inch-wide electric motor installed between the turbine and compressor wheels is designed to eliminate turbocharging delay by maintaining high turbocharger pressure and boost pressure even at low engine speeds. AMG engineers say that the system provides 45-50 percent response at low revs and 10-15 percent better response at high revs.<br>Developed in conjunction with Garrett, the turbocharged C43 is the first electric exhaust turbocharger ever installed on a production car. Mercedes-AMG attaches great importance to the fact that turbocharging is a technology directly borrowed from Formula 1, although in fact it is the idea of using an electric motor to maintain the rotation of the turbocharger, and not the equipment itself inspired by Formula 1. About 70 percent of the parts in the C43 turbocharger are the same as in a conventional exhaust-driven turbocharger.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Advantages and disadvantages</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It is true that there is no noticeable turbo lag anywhere in the rev range. The 2.0-liter four-cylinder engine responds quickly to pressing the throttle, but this response is strangely muted. The C43 effortlessly overcomes any road at a fast pace thanks to a well-matched chassis, Michelin Pilot Sport 4S tires and an impressive grip with the standard 4Matic all-wheel drive system, which provides a fixed torque distribution of 31% in front and 69% in the rear. Still, it doesn\'t look like he has just over 400 horses under the hood.<br>In fact, the problem may be more related to torque than power: the M139L not only develops 30 Nm less torque than the 3.0-liter twin-turbo V-6 of the previous C43, but its peak torque is 3,000 rpm higher in the RPM range, 5,000 rpm per minute compared to the V-6 costs 2000.<br>Mercedes-AMG claims that the acceleration time of the new C43 from a standstill to 100 km/h is 4.6 seconds on the way to the maximum speed limited by electronics. The C43 that we tested in 2017, which was equipped with the original 362-horsepower version of the V-6, and not the later 385-horsepower engine, showed the time is 4.2 seconds.<br>And this is despite the fact that the new car has a multi-position nine-speed AMG Speedshift MCT transmission, which is said to provide faster gear changes than the usual nine-speed automatic connected to the old V-6.<br>The 2023 Mercedes-AMG C43 is a good AMG performance sedan, but not a great AMG performance sedan. While the chassis—steering, braking, maneuverability, grip and traction—are awesome, the engine doesn\'t deliver the thrills we expect from AMG. It\'s competent, but not exciting, and in this case less doesn\'t mean more.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Mercedes-AMG C43 2023 Test Drive', 'The magic of modern automotive mathematics: the Mercedes-AMG C43 engine of 2023, the entry-level Mercedes C-Class line, produces almost 5 percent more power than the one that powered the previous', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'mercedes-amg-c43-2023-test-drive', '', '', '2022-11-19 19:03:25', '2022-11-19 16:03:25', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=670', 0, 'post', '', 0),
