(673, 2, '2022-11-19 19:08:20', '2022-11-19 16:08:20', '<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We can say that the hopes, wishes and prayers of enthusiasts and fans of the brand about the Porsche 911 SUV have been heard and realized.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Having visited any Porsche auto show over the past few years, we were presented with the so-called \"Safari 911\". A typical assembly included a lifting kit, off-road tires, a safety frame and a spare wheel that could be hung on the roof for added credibility. We say the \"so-called\" 911 Safari because it was never a production Porsche model, but rather an ephemeral general description of the fortified, race-ready 911s that participated in the long-distance off-road rally decades ago, and, well, their modern versions are a kind of homage.<br>Now Porsche has joined this fun in earnest, releasing 2500 models of the 911 Dakar based on its 911 sports car. The addition, which follows the name of the rear-engined car model, is a reference to the Paris-Dakar Rally of 1984, a grueling off-road race in which Porsche took the top step of the podium. So, what special touches did Porsche include in the production of the first ever off-road sports car 911?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>More than just a high Carrera</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Why arrange a safari - uh, Dakar, now? According to Achim Lamparter, Porsche\'s chassis development manager for the 911 and 718, \"The Safari you see on the road has undoubtedly influenced us because we are all Porsche fans. We have the same ideas, and we know what the fans want. It was just the next step.\"<br>Porsche itself will say that the most obvious change compared to the usual 911 is the 50-millimeter Dakar lift, which is only 5 centimeters. In case it is necessary to increase the ground clearance, Porsche has also equipped the 911 Dakar with a standard lifting kit that can additionally lift the car by 30 millimeters. The standard ground clearance is 16 centimeters, and the maximum increased one reaches 19 cm. According to Porsche, in the mode of increasing the height of the 911 Dakar will easily reach speeds of up to 160 km / h, after which it will return to its standard ground clearance.<br>The Carrera 4 GTS transmission is actually located under the raised body. Its 3.0-liter twin-turbocharged six-cylinder engine produces a healthy 473 hp and 569 Nm of torque. With the help of an all-wheel drive system and an eight-speed automatic transmission with dual clutch, the car accelerates from a standstill to 100 km/h in 3.2 seconds and the maximum speed is up to 240 km/h with limited tire consumption.<br>The off-road and rally modes are unique to this 911 and they replace the Sport+ and Individual modes that are commonly found on the 911 GTS. The first one is better suited for providing improved traction and crawling, because when turned on, it provides maximum travel height. The latter option is better suited for loose surfaces. Porsche has equipped the 911 Dakar with the rally launch control system, which provides maximum wheel slip of up to 20% on surfaces with low grip. Those hoping to enjoy their 911 on the asphalt need not worry, as Porsche has developed its rally-capable sports car at the Nurburgring and the Weissach test track.<br>Porsche has adopted the carbon hood, steering on the rear axle and engine supports from the 911 GT3, and also equipped it with the Porsche Dynamic chassis control system, which provides additional opportunities for high-performance driving both off-road and on asphalt. Cooling is carried out using the same (probably redundant) system as in the 911 Turbo and Turbo S. The lockable center differential provides even greater cross-country capability. Porsche took measures not to increase the weight of the 911 Dakar: full carbon fiber bucket seats, removed rear seats and lightweight glass helped to maintain a curb weight of 1,611 kilograms, which, according to the brand, is only 7 kilograms more than the automatic 911 Carrera 4 GTS.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Ready to hit the road</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Other off-road equipment includes front and rear tow hooks, stainless steel protective plates at the front, rear and side, as well as a bottom panel made of carbon fiber reinforced polymers to protect the underside of the car. Mesh grilles protecting the air intakes give stainless steel another look.<br>As an option, a roof rack with a dynamic load capacity of 41 kg is offered. Porsche uses a 12-volt outlet to power the taillights on the trunk for rally-style road lighting. For additional equipment of the trunk, Porsche offers a variety of technical equipment options so that car owners do not have to buy them in the secondary market.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Another \"more special\" option</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The standard 2023 Porsche 911 Dakar offers typical customization options that buyers have come to expect from the brand\'s products. The shade of green paint is unique for this particular model, and the standard interior is complemented by contrasting stitching of the same color. The 19- and 20-inch offset alloy wheels are inspired by the classic Fuchs wheels that were installed on historic Porsche 911 models.<br>Buyers who want to get deeper into the rally heritage of the 911 Dakar can choose the Rallye Design kit, which directly borrows the ideas of the Porsche racing car that won the Paris-Dakar Rally in 1984. The exterior is painted in white and gentian-blue metallic with red and gold stripes. Instead of placing the inscription \"Rothmans\" on top of the livery imitating Rothmans, as on a rally car in 1984, the new car comes with a fairly similar \"Roughroad\" graphics as a kind of replacement. Racing numbers are available and they can be assigned numbers from 1 to 999. Porsche is Porsche, so there are also several suitable wristwatches available.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>How to buy it?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Porsche declined to say whether all 2,500 units have been purchased, but indicated that customers can contact dealers to receive orders now. The 2023 911 Dakar will appear on showgrounds in the spring of 2023 at a staggering price of $223,450. If all of the above suits you, we suggest contacting dealers as soon as possible: it looks like Dakar is everything Porsche fans wanted in the 911 inspired rally.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'The first look of the Porsche 911 Dakar 2023: the fantasy of an SUV is embodied', 'Having visited any Porsche auto show over the past few years, we were presented with the so-called \"Safari 911\". A typical assembly included a lifting kit, off-road tires, a safety frame and a spare wheel that ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-first-look-of-the-porsche-911-dakar-2023-the-fantasy-of-an-suv-is-embodied', '', '', '2022-11-19 19:12:26', '2022-11-19 16:12:26', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=673', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(674, 1, '2022-11-19 19:08:15', '2022-11-19 16:08:15', '', '034-hswi-porsche-911-dakar-2023-jpg-1-991-2521-945-1000x562', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '034-hswi-porsche-911-dakar-2023-jpg-1-991-2521-945-1000x562', '', '', '2022-11-19 19:08:15', '2022-11-19 16:08:15', '', 673, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/034-hswi-porsche-911-dakar-2023-jpg-1-991-2521-945-1000x562-1.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
