(676, 2, '2022-11-19 19:12:14', '2022-11-19 16:12:14', '<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The new 911 GT3 RS is painted white with green accents in honor of the first high-performance street 911</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The 1972-73 Porsche 911 Carrera RS 2.7 introduced enough engine and aerodynamics innovations to make it the fastest racing track 911 ever built at the factory, and its iconic \"duck tail\" spoiler captured the imagination of fans. This spirit of improved performance is preserved in the GT3 RS 2023, which received its own engine settings and aerodynamic innovations, including the highest wing ever installed on the 911 - and now an additional edition has been created, in which the link between generations looks even more clear. Porsche presents its customers with an exclusive set of Porsche 911 GT3 RS Tribute 2023 — a special high-quality finish and painting that pays homage to the original high-performance Porsche of fifty years ago.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Starting point</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It all looks familiar because Porsche unveiled the look of this car back in August at Quail, a motorsport event as part of this year\'s Monterey Car Week. Obviously, there was enough interest from customers to pack it up and sell it..<br>Having just completed the new fastest lap on the Nurburgring-Nordschleife circuit, Porsche has a lot to celebrate with the modern incarnation of this latest RS. The sports car boasts a 4.0-liter atmospheric six-cylinder engine with a capacity of 518 horsepower and a torque of 469 Nm, as well as a set of aerodynamic solutions, including the active aero package, used for the first time on a road car.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>A tribute to the 911 GT3 RS</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In honor of the original, the new GT3 RS Tribute kit is equipped with side and rear graphics, mirror caps and magnesium disks painted in python green (the original color was called \"Viper\"). These accents are scattered across the white base coat and are combined with glossy black brake calipers and small American flags on the wing end plates, thanks to which the Tribute looks like it is racing into battle.<br>These Tribute-style changes are based on the Weissach package, which is already available on the standard GT3 RS, and which offers body parts such as the hood, roof panel, mirrors and part of the wing made of carbon fiber, as well as some chassis components made of carbon fiber reinforced polymers (CFRP), for additional weight savings. and giving more rigidity.<br>The GT3 RS Tribute package features new illuminated door sills, translated from English as \"Homage to the Carrera RS\", an embossed RS logo on the center console cover, as well as carbon fiber trim elements included in the Weissach package. The interior materials are a combination of leather and Race-Tex fabric, now with green thread stitching on the seats and dashboard.<br>Porsche says the Tribute to Carrera RS package is available to \"customers who already own a 911 GT3 RS,\" and its total cost after delivery will be $314,000.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Additional bonuses</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If the question of buying this car still sounds a little frivolous (not taking into account the incredible design of the base model, before moving on to aesthetics), do not worry — this edition goes beyond a simple sports car. If GT3 RS buyers get a magnesium alloy wristwatch included, those who also buy the Tribute model will receive a custom-made python-colored watch with a white bezel and a strap stitch to match the interior.<br>Also, the new buyer will receive a car case, a keychain and valve caps with the inscription Python Green, custom—made license plate frames, as well as two model copies of the original 1973 Carrera RS, as well as the new GT3 RS Tribute in 1:43 scale. And if one of the owners really wants, the kit will include new NFT badges as \"digital souvenirs\" from Porsche race tracks and competitions, a kind of virtual trophy collection. If that sounds too hard to imagine, achievements in competitions are also accompanied by physical rewards.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Porsche 911 GT3 RS 2023 test drive in honor of the iconic 1973 Carrera RS', 'The 1972-73 Porsche 911 Carrera RS 2.7 introduced enough engine and aerodynamics innovations to make it the fastest racing track 911 ever built at the factory, and its iconic \"duck tail\" spoiler captured the ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'porsche-911-gt3-rs-2023-test-drive-in-honor-of-the-iconic-1973-carrera-rs', '', '', '2022-11-19 19:12:14', '2022-11-19 16:12:14', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=676', 0, 'post', '', 0),
