(679, 2, '2022-11-19 19:16:00', '2022-11-19 16:16:00', '<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Porsche\'s 434 hp Macan GTS defies stereotypes about SUVs and behaves like a high-performance car</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For those who are looking for a sports car, but also an SUV, there is a solution — Porsche. The Macan GTS 2022 has sticky tires that stick to the asphalt like leeches. At an engine speed of 4900 per minute, this all-wheel drive SUV accelerates to 100 kilometers per hour faster than the mid-engined Boxster 718 S. And its steering is so precise that you can splash through puddles in the parking lot and use wet tires to write love notes in italics to the engineers who brought such a car to life.<br>The Porsche GTS models have always been the benchmark in their model range, regardless of whether we are talking about sports cars, sedans or SUVs. Usually sandwiched between the S and Turbo versions, it perfectly combines handling and power. But, at least at the moment, Macan GTS is not an ordinary porridge for a bear cub. New in 2022, the GTS inherited the 434-horsepower 2.9-liter twin-turbocharged V-6 of last year\'s Macan Turbo and took this model\'s place as the hottest dish.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>How fast is the Porsche Macan GTS?</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The GTS accelerates from a standstill to 100 km/h in 3.6 seconds, and it takes 12.2 seconds to fly four hundred meters (a quarter of a mile) — this is the fastest Macan car that we have ever tested. (We\'ve never had a chance to test the turbocharged model that the GTS replaces.) This speed is directly transferred from the highway to the road, where it is almost impossible to catch the engine sleeping. We squeeze out the gas, and the Macan begins to act with a lightning-fast shift to a lower gear, which reminds us that not only 434 horsepower and 550 Nm of torque make this car so cool, but also a seven-speed Porsche dual-clutch transmission.<br>When the road becomes twisty and the speed limits decrease, the impressions only get stronger. Adaptive shock absorbers and reinforced pneumatic springs that lower the body by 1 cm are included as standard in the GTS, while the $12,010 sports package includes braking-based torque control and 21-inch wheels shod in Pirelli P Zero Corsa PZC4 tires, which are wider on the rear axle than on the the front. All this gives lateral grip on the uneven asphalt of our skid pad up to 0.96 g. On smooth asphalt, the car is easily held on the road at 1-g, and this is an SUV!<br>However, I would not be quite right if I said that the Macan is driven like a sports car. Because of these staggered tires, heavy weight distribution, and torque distribution to all four wheels, the GTS does not provide such an even balance of front and rear grip as the 911, Cayman, or Boxster does. In many ways, and I say this as a compliment, the Macan GTS drives just like the world\'s best Volkswagen GTI. It is infinitely predictable, it is so easy to place it where you want, and it changes direction with supernatural speed. It\'s exciting, and yet using these features effortlessly can make the trip even more exciting. In addition, the daily use of expensive and fast—wearing Corsa tires for the driver seems like a stupid decision - even in the most idyllic climate.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>\"Small\" troubles</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In many ways, the Macan is a weird little SUV. Is it too small? Too low to be called an SUV? Why does it look like a retractor has been inserted into its grille? However, it is not worth thinking about these questions for a long time, because the best Porsche cars are always a little \"strange\".<br>The Macan also has a simpler physical feel of compactness. Its external dimensions are comparable to BMW X3 M and Mercedes-AMG GLC 63, and yet if you stand next to a Macan with four adults, you can be surprised if their only task is to squeeze into a clown car.<br>It takes a little gymnastics to get through the narrow doorways, and the center console does take up space for the driver\'s and front passenger\'s legs, but there is a little more space inside than you might expect. Four of our adults will still fit, although it may not be easy to squeeze their luggage in.<br>On the other hand, Porsche\'s infotainment system and capacitive touchscreen still seem wrong after more than a decade of using this system. It doesn\'t seem like a Porsche, having so many settings - the stiffness of the shock absorbers, stability control and active exhaust, among other things — located so far away on the center console, behind the gearshift lever. Since they cannot be identified by touch, you have to stretch your neck and lower your eyes to find what you need, taking your eyes off the road for too long.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>The price of \"almost perfection\"</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The price for the Macan GTS starts at $84,350. Even the proven price of this particular GTS of $98,950 seems reasonable considering what we\'re getting, namely an experience that few other SUVs can match. There are of course other SUVs that can simulate Macan acceleration and cornering skills. Few of them feel so natural at the same time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Porsche Macan GTS 2022 Test Drive: So fast, so tenacious, so good', 'For those who are looking for a sports car, but also an SUV, there is a solution — Porsche. The Macan GTS 2022 has sticky tires that stick to the asphalt like leeches. At an engine speed of 4900 per minute, this', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'porsche-macan-gts-2022-test-drive-so-fast-so-tenacious-so-good', '', '', '2022-11-19 19:16:00', '2022-11-19 16:16:00', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=679', 0, 'post', '', 0),
