65 mm, in turn increasing the length of the car itself by 5715 mm — only 47 mm less than the standard Phantom wheelbase. The Ghost also weighs 2553 kg in the standard form and 2599 kg in the extended model.<br>To be honest, from the point of view of the comfort level of the passengers of the \"ghost\", you are unlikely to be dissatisfied. No seat lacks space, even in the shorter of the two body options.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Trunk</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You won\'t be able to carry cabinets on it, but for ordinary luggage, the 507-liter Ghost space should be enough. However, it really shrinks if you check the box for the refrigerator option “central refrigerator\".</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Reliability and safety</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Unsurprisingly, no one has crashed a Ghost on a crash test yet, but the safety should still be excellent, and the service and warranty coverage comprehensive.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Service</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are no defined maintenance intervals for the Ghost, and condition-based maintenance means that the car itself controls various criteria. Rolls-Royce also offers owners two-, three- and five-year service packages after the four-year warranty period.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Rolls Royce Ghost — Luxury Car review', 'While the Phantom remains the most luxurious car, and Cullinan has opened Rolls-Royce to a completely new market, you can still get that unforgettable experience from owning the long-known luxury Rolls—', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '688-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-11-19 20:21:58', '2022-11-19 17:21:58', '', 688, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=690', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(691, 2, '2022-11-19 20:32:06', '2022-11-19 17:32:06', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We are big fans of the Range Rover Sport. This is one of the most popular premium SUVs currently available, and deservedly so: this car is great in terms of sports driving. It fully lives up to its name, standing out for its high performance and challenging size and weight stability control and control systems.<br>The Range Rover Sport is as luxurious as you would expect from a large car with the Range Rover logo. There is little to find fault with and a lot to like: many car owners are ready to recommend it to others.<br>The Range Rover Sport was first introduced in 2005 as a more fashionable and affordable alternative to the full-size Range Rover. This allowed the larger model to move further into the market, and the sport competed with cars such as the Porsche Cayenne and BMW X5.<br>The current model, launched in 2013, is the second generation of the Range Rover Sport. When the original model was based on the same platform as the Land Rover Discovery — the car was very heavy, the new model is all aluminum and much lighter. This brings solid advantages both on the road and off-road, and Sport is an amazingly capable vehicle, wherever you go, given its size.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Handling, engines and performance</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The second generation Range Rover Sport has really advanced in terms of drive and dynamics. The brand new, all-aluminum architecture is very rigid and durable, and the improved suspension design and the perfect all-wheel drive system give a driving experience that is unlikely to disappoint.<br>The Range Rover Sport\'s abilities are obvious initially. Although the steering is a bit light, it is also extremely precise and crisp, which makes it easy to drive this big car both in the city and on winding roads without asphalt. The balance is clearly defined, the Rover never feels heavy or blurry while driving, and usually gives control and composure that would amaze those who dismiss it as a big, heavy 4x4 SUV.<br>All Range Rover sports models are supplied as standard with a height-adjustable standard air suspension and an adaptive dynamic Land Rover system. This system adjusts the suspension operation in accordance with road conditions, and also includes a dynamic mode that minimizes body roll and maximizes traction. Of course, as a result, the ride becomes tougher, but the driving qualities are perfectly fine-tuned in normal mode, with incomparable body control, sufficient ability to absorb road bumps and amazing stability. Dynamically, the Range Rover Sport is not much different from the superb.<br>Thanks to Land Rover\'s incomparable off-road pedigree, the Range Rover Sport\'s abilities surpass those of its rivals when it comes to off-road driving. It is equipped with an electronic central differential and Land Rover\'s smart terrain response system, which optimizes the car\'s settings for driving on dirt, gravel, snow, rocks and sand by changing the suspension height, gearbox settings, throttle response and traction control profiles. Despite the size and weight of the car, the combination of robust chassis components and smart electronics gives this large SUV impressive off-road performance.<br>Even riding on water should not bring unpleasant surprises, it is allowed to wade up to an 85-centimeter depth — there is even a gadget that shows how deep you are driving on water, this is just a dream of Russian off-road youtubers. There are a huge number of videos on the Internet with cars stuck in reservoirs.<br>Dynamic HSE models and higher are supplied with an improved Terrain Response 2 system — it includes automatic sensing of the terrain to select the correct control mode. The JLR All-Terrain Response Control system is also used on dynamic models. This is a kind of \"off-road cruise control\" that allows the driver to choose the right speed and leave all the hard work to the car.<br>The SVR model is a completely different matter, definitely performance—oriented, it has massive wheels, large brakes, rigid suspension and a lot of complex developments in everything that gives the car performance. The simple fact that its maximum speed has been increased to 260 km/h should show the level of development of this 2.5-ton machine.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Engines</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The P400 version uses a straight six-cylinder petrol engine that produces 395 hp using a 48-volt soft hybrid system. This is an engine that fills the car with smooth, powerful performance, especially in its low and medium range — with an acceleration time from 0 to 100 kilometers per hour in 5.9 seconds and a maximum speed of 225 km/h. The same soft hybrid technology is included in the diesel variants of the D300 and D350, resulting in an acceleration time of 7.3 seconds and 6.9 seconds, respectively.<br>As part of the 2018 update, Land Rover introduced a plug-in hybrid version of the PHEV from Jaguar Land Rover. Wearing the P400e badge, the Range Rover Sport is powered by a 2.0-liter turbocharged gasoline engine with a capacity of 296 hp and an 85 kW electric motor providing a total power of 398 hp and 640 Nm of torque.<br>It has the claimed ability to travel up to 40 kilometers on a single electric drive with a maximum speed of 136 km/h. It will also add 5.0-liter V8 power, and as a result, the car accelerates from a standstill to 100 km / h in 6.3 seconds, and the maximum speed is 220 km / h.<br>Many may be tempted by the attractive-sounding supercharged gasoline V8, which even in the \"basic\" version produces 518 hp. Acceleration of the car from a place to a hundred is provided in 5.3 seconds.<br>However, the 567 hp SVR is even faster, making the benchmark sprint in just 4.5 seconds, with absolutely perfect V8 sound in the background. This is an exciting productive machine.<br>All Range Rover Sport models are equipped with an excellent eight-speed automatic transmission.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Design and technology</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The interior of the Range Rover Sport leaves no doubt that this is a real luxury car. Even in the standard guise, the trim has stripes of chic Oxford leather, jewel-like switches and a central widescreen display.<br>This is a more sporty layout than the formal Range Rover – and for this version it was made from scratch (the previous model shared an interior with the Land Rover Discovery). It looks like a more chic, more adult Range Rover Evoque, in such cars it\'s nice to just sit inside.<br>The only problem is that, despite all this luxury, the technology is not as modern as it could be.<br>But the generous design makes up for it. You can also fully customize the premium Range Rover Sport with even more luxurious options with leather trim and a wide range of decorative elements. A projection display is also available that shows speed, gear selector position, cruise control information, road sign recognition and direction from satellite navigation.<br>The regular HSE contains everything you will ever need as standard: satellite navigation, xenon headlights, Oxford leather, heated front seats, front and rear parking sensors, electric trunk door and adaptive dynamic suspension. 20-inch alloy wheels are also standard.<br>The most refined model is the Autobiography Dynamic, which has a panoramic glass roof, glossy black exterior styling elements, semi-aniline leather 22-way adjustable front seats with ventilation and a cooler for the front center console. SVR, meanwhile, lives up to its leading position in the lineup with a range of technology, luxury and performance.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Infotainment system</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The long-awaited Touch Pro Duo twin infotainment system with a 10-inch touchscreen appeared as part of the 2018 update, and this is a huge improvement over the outdated old system. In addition, the ability to connect mobile devices in the car using up to 12 power points, including two internal sockets for charging laptops and other devices, has been improved.<br>Meridian\'s standard surround sound system is excellent, with the purity of a concert hall and enormous depth.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Practicality</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Despite the fact that the Range Rover Sport is not as big as the flagship Range Rover, the interior is still very flexible and comfortable for the family. This is a great everyday car that can accommodate up to seven people without fuss.<br>However, the absolute comfort of the Range Rover Sport stands out even more. The beautifully and generously trimmed leather cabin, even in the standard HSE finish, with decent quality and fit, gives pleasure from traveling any distance.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Size</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Range Rover Sport is a big car, even though it\'s smaller than a full-size Range Rover. Sport has a length of 4850 mm, a width of 2073 mm and a height of 1780 mm: there are not so many cars on the road with a width of more than two meters and a height of almost 1.8 meters.<br>Speaking in the context of competition, the BMW X5 has a length of 4,886 mm, a width of 1,938 mm and a height of 1,762 mm (with a 650-liter trunk), and the Porsche Cayenne has an almost identical length of 4,885 mm, a width of 1,939 mm and a height of 1,705 mm (with a 618—liter trunk).<br>However, despite this size, owners find the Sport easy to drive, probably because Land Rover has developed such precise steering and installed front and rear parking sensors as standard.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Free space for passengers and trunk</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A large Range Rover Sport is a spacious car for passengers. The air suspension can be lowered by 50 mm to assist entry and exit, and once inside, passengers can appreciate the comfort provided, which uniquely corresponds to a high level of expectation.<br>The driver has the feeling that he is not sitting \"inside\" the car, but inside the tower, looking down at other cars thanks to the beautiful view from the front and through the large side windows. Needless to say, the driver\'s seat is spacious and fully adjustable.<br>The passengers in the back seats are not bad either. The high seats are comfortable and spacious – they are great for long trips, unless of course you are lucky enough to be on two external seats (the middle seat is less comfortable). There is plenty of room for legs and head, even in dynamic models that come with a standard panoramic roof.<br>The third row is usually a bit more difficult to access, and once you\'re there, it becomes clear why Land Rover calls it a 5+2 and not a real seven-seater like the Mercedes-Benz GLS.<br>The trunk is a huge 784 liters in a five-seat appearance, which increases to 1761 liters with folded seats in the middle row. However, in the seven-seat version it is much smaller.<br>Please also note that the seven-seat version does not get a full-size spare wheel, as there is simply no space for it under the rear seats. This is what you need to know if you are going to go off-road, where tires may be at risk of punctures.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Towing</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Most regular Range Rover Sport models have a sufficient towing capacity of 3,500 kg, but the hybrid is limited to 2,500 kg, while the 2.0-liter P300 and performance SVR models are capable of towing 3,000 kg.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Range Rover Sport 2020 — detailed review', 'We are big fans of the Range Rover Sport. This is one of the most popular premium SUVs currently available, and deservedly so: this car is great in terms of sports driving. It fully lives up to its name, ', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'range-rover-sport-2020-detailed-review', '', '', '2022-11-19 20:32:06', '2022-11-19 17:32:06', '', 0, 'http://wordpress-carbook-training.ru/?p=691', 0, 'post', '', 0),
